1 // ImGui library v1.14 wip
2 // See ImGui::ShowTestWindow() for sample code.
3 // Read 'Programmer guide' below for notes on how to setup ImGui in your codebase.
4 // Get latest version at https://github.com/ocornut/imgui
5 // Developped by Omar Cornut and contributors.
6 
7 /*
8 
9  MISSION STATEMENT
10  =================
11 
12  - easy to use to create code-driven and data-driven tools
13  - easy to use to create adhoc short-lived tools and long-lived, more elaborate tools
14  - easy to hack and improve
15  - minimize screen real-estate usage
16  - minimize setup and maintainance
17  - minimize state storage on user side
18  - portable, minimize dependencies, run on target (consoles, etc.)
19  - efficient runtime (nb- we do allocate when "growing" content - creating a window / opening a tree node for the first time, etc. - but a typical frame won't allocate anything)
20  - read about immediate-mode GUI principles @ http://mollyrocket.com/861, http://mollyrocket.com/forums/index.html
21 
22  Designed for developers and content-creators, not the typical end-user! Some of the weaknesses includes:
23  - doesn't look fancy, doesn't animate
24  - limited layout features, intricate layouts are typically crafted in code
25  - occasionally use statically sized buffers for string manipulations - won't crash, but some long text may be clipped
26 
27  END-USER GUIDE
28  ==============
29 
30  - double-click title bar to collapse window
31  - click upper right corner to close a window, available when 'bool* open' is passed to ImGui::Begin()
32  - click and drag on lower right corner to resize window
33  - click and drag on any empty space to move window
34  - double-click/double-tap on lower right corner grip to auto-fit to content
35  - TAB/SHIFT+TAB to cycle through keyboard editable fields
36  - use mouse wheel to scroll
37  - use CTRL+mouse wheel to zoom window contents (if IO.FontAllowScaling is true)
38  - CTRL+Click on a slider to input value as text
39  - text editor:
40  - Hold SHIFT or use mouse to select text.
41  - CTRL+Left/Right to word jump
42  - CTRL+Shift+Left/Right to select words
43  - CTRL+A our Double-Click to select all
44  - CTRL+X,CTRL+C,CTRL+V to use OS clipboard
45  - CTRL+Z,CTRL+Y to undo/redo
46  - ESCAPE to revert text to its original value
47  - You can apply arithmetic operators +,*,/ on numerical values. Use +- to subtract (because - would set a negative value!)
48 
49  PROGRAMMER GUIDE
50  ================
51 
52  - your code creates the UI, if your code doesn't run the UI is gone! == dynamic UI, no construction step, less data retention on your side, no state duplication, less sync, less errors.
53  - see ImGui::ShowTestWindow() for user-side sample code
54  - see examples/ folder for standalone sample applications.
55 
56  - getting started:
57  - initialisation: call ImGui::GetIO() and fill the 'Settings' data.
58  - every frame:
59  1/ in your mainloop or right after you got your keyboard/mouse info, call ImGui::GetIO() and fill the 'Input' data, then call ImGui::NewFrame().
60  2/ use any ImGui function you want between NewFrame() and Render()
61  3/ ImGui::Render() to render all the accumulated command-lists. it will call your RenderDrawListFn handler that you set in the IO structure.
62  - all rendering information are stored into command-lists until ImGui::Render() is called.
63  - effectively it means you can create widgets at any time in your code, regardless of "update" vs "render" considerations.
64  - refer to the examples applications in the examples/ folder for instruction on how to setup your code.
65  - a typical application skeleton may be:
66 
67  // Application init
68  // TODO: Fill all settings fields of the io structure
69  ImGuiIO& io = ImGui::GetIO();
70  io.DisplaySize.x = 1920.0f;
71  io.DisplaySize.y = 1280.0f;
72  io.DeltaTime = 1.0f/60.0f;
73  io.IniFilename = "imgui.ini";
74 
75  // Application mainloop
76  while (true)
77  {
78  // 1/ get low-level input
79  // e.g. on Win32, GetKeyboardState(), or poll your events, etc.
80 
81  // 2/ TODO: Fill all 'Input' fields of io structure and call NewFrame
82  ImGuiIO& io = ImGui::GetIO();
83  io.MousePos = ...
84  io.KeysDown[i] = ...
85  ImGui::NewFrame();
86 
87  // 3/ most of your application code here - you can use any of ImGui::* functions between NewFrame() and Render() calls
88  GameUpdate();
89  GameRender();
90 
91  // 4/ render & swap video buffers
92  ImGui::Render();
93  // swap video buffer, etc.
94  }
95 
96  TROUBLESHOOTING & FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
97  ============================================
98 
99  - if text or lines are blurry when integrating ImGui in your engine:
100  - in your Render function, try translating your projection matrix by (0.5f,0.5f) or (0.375f,0.375f)
101  - try adjusting ImGui::GetIO().PixelCenterOffset to 0.5f or 0.375f
102 
103  - if you can only see text but no solid shapes or lines:
104  - make sure io.FontTexUvForWhite is set to the texture coordinates of a pure white pixel in your texture.
105  (this is done for you if you are using the default font)
106  (ImGui is using this texture coordinate to draw solid objects so text and solid draw calls can be merged into one.)
107 
108  - if you want to use a different font than the default:
109  - create bitmap font data using BMFont, make sure that BMFont is exporting the .fnt file in Binary mode.
110  io.Font = new ImBitmapFont();
111  io.Font->LoadFromFile("path_to_your_fnt_file.fnt");
112  - load your texture yourself. texture *MUST* have white pixel at UV coordinate io.FontTexUvForWhite. This is used to draw all solid shapes.
113  - the extra_fonts/ folder provides examples of using external fonts.
114 
115  - if you are confused about the meaning or use of ID in ImGui:
116  - some widgets requires state to be carried over multiple frames (most typically ImGui often wants remember what is the "active" widget).
117  to do so they need an unique ID. unique ID are typically derived from a string label, an indice or a pointer.
118  when you call Button("OK") the button shows "OK" and also use "OK" as an ID.
119  - ID are uniquely scoped within Windows so no conflict can happen if you have two buttons called "OK" in two different Windows.
120  within a same Window, use PushID() / PopID() to easily create scopes and avoid ID conflicts.
121  so if you have a loop creating "multiple" items, you can use PushID() / PopID() with the index of each item, or their pointer, etc.
122  some functions like TreeNode() implicitly creates a scope for you by calling PushID()
123  - when dealing with trees, ID are important because you want to preserve the opened/closed state of tree nodes.
124  depending on your use cases you may want to use strings, indices or pointers as ID. experiment and see what makes more sense!
125  e.g. When displaying a single object, using a static string as ID will preserve your node open/closed state when the targetted object change
126  e.g. When displaying a list of objects, using indices or pointers as ID will preserve the node open/closed state per object
127  - when passing a label you can optionally specify extra unique ID information within the same string using "##". This helps solving the simpler collision cases.
128  e.g. "Label" display "Label" and uses "Label" as ID
129  e.g. "Label##Foobar" display "Label" and uses "Label##Foobar" as ID
130  e.g. "##Foobar" display an empty label and uses "##Foobar" as ID
131  - read articles about the imgui principles (see web links) to understand the requirement and use of ID.
132 
133  - tip: the construct 'if (IMGUI_ONCE_UPON_A_FRAME)' will evaluate to true only once a frame, you can use it to add custom UI in the middle of a deep nested inner loop in your code.
134  - tip: you can call Render() multiple times (e.g for VR renders), up to you to communicate the extra state to your RenderDrawListFn function.
135  - tip: you can create widgets without a Begin()/End() block, they will go in an implicit window called "Debug"
136  - tip: read the ShowTestWindow() code for more example of how to use ImGui!
137 
138  API BREAKING CHANGES
139  ====================
140 
141  - 2014/09/25 (1.13) removed 'text_end' parameter from IO.SetClipboardTextFn (the string is now always zero-terminated for simplicity)
142  - 2014/09/24 (1.12) renamed SetFontScale() to SetWindowFontScale()
143  - 2014/09/24 (1.12) moved IM_MALLOC/IM_REALLOC/IM_FREE preprocessor defines to IO.MemAllocFn/IO.MemReallocFn/IO.MemFreeFn
144  - 2014/08/30 (1.09) removed IO.FontHeight (now computed automatically)
145  - 2014/08/30 (1.09) moved IMGUI_FONT_TEX_UV_FOR_WHITE preprocessor define to IO.FontTexUvForWhite
146  - 2014/08/28 (1.09) changed the behaviour of IO.PixelCenterOffset following various rendering fixes

312 ImGuiIO::ImGuiIO()
313 {

315  DeltaTime = 1.0f/60.0f;
316  IniSavingRate = 5.0f;
317  IniFilename = "imgui.ini";
318  LogFilename = "imgui_log.txt";
319  Font = NULL;
320  FontYOffset = 0.0f;
321  FontTexUvForWhite = ImVec2(0.0f,0.0f);
322  FontBaseScale = 1.0f;
323  FontAllowUserScaling = false;
324  FontFallbackGlyph = (ImWchar)'?';
325  PixelCenterOffset = 0.0f;
326  MousePos = ImVec2(-1,-1);
327  MousePosPrev = ImVec2(-1,-1);
328  MouseDoubleClickTime = 0.30f;
329  MouseDoubleClickMaxDist = 6.0f;
330

332  RenderDrawListsFn = NULL;
333  MemAllocFn = malloc;
334  MemReallocFn = realloc;
335  MemFreeFn = free;
336  GetClipboardTextFn = GetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl; // Platform dependant default implementations
337  SetClipboardTextFn = SetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl;
338  ImeSetInputScreenPosFn = NULL;
339 }

341 // Pass in translated ASCII characters for text input.
342 // - with glfw you can get those from the callback set in glfwSetCharCallback()
343 // - on Windows you can get those using ToAscii+keyboard state, or via the VM_CHAR message
344 static size_t ImStrlenW(const ImWchar* str);
345 void ImGuiIO::AddInputCharacter(ImWchar c)
346 {
347  const size_t n = ImStrlenW(InputCharacters);
348  if (n < sizeof(InputCharacters) / sizeof(InputCharacters[0]))
349  {
350  InputCharacters[n] = c;
351  InputCharacters[n+1] = 0;
352  }
353 }

370 // Math bits
371 // We are keeping those static in the .cpp file so as not to leak them outside, in the case the user has implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and its own types.
372 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x*rhs, lhs.y*rhs); }
373 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x/rhs, lhs.y/rhs); }
374 static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x+rhs.x, lhs.y+rhs.y); }
375 static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x-rhs.x, lhs.y-rhs.y); }
376 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2 rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x*rhs.x, lhs.y*rhs.y); }
377 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2 rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x/rhs.x, lhs.y/rhs.y); }
378 static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
379 static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
380 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
381 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
382 
383 static inline int ImMin(int lhs, int rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
384 static inline int ImMax(int lhs, int rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
385 static inline float ImMin(float lhs, float rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
386 static inline float ImMax(float lhs, float rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
387 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(ImMin(lhs.x,rhs.x), ImMin(lhs.y,rhs.y)); }
388 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(ImMax(lhs.x,rhs.x), ImMax(lhs.y,rhs.y)); }
389 static inline float ImClamp(float f, float mn, float mx) { return (f < mn) ? mn : (f > mx) ? mx : f; }
390 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& f, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2(ImClamp(f.x,mn.x,mx.x), ImClamp(f.y,mn.y,mx.y)); }
391 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
392 static inline float ImLerp(float a, float b, float t) { return a + (b - a) * t; }
393 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return a + (b - a) * t; }
394 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
395 static inline float ImLength(const ImVec2& lhs) { return sqrt(lhs.x*lhs.x + lhs.y*lhs.y); }
396

402 static int ImStricmp(const char* str1, const char* str2)
403 {
404  int d;
405  while ((d = toupper(*str2) - toupper(*str1)) == 0 && *str1) { str1++; str2++; }
406  return d;
407 }

409 static char* ImStrdup(const char *str)
410 {
411  char *buff = (char*)ImGui::MemAlloc(strlen(str) + 1);
412  IM_ASSERT(buff);
413  strcpy(buff, str);
414  return buff;
415 }

417 static size_t ImStrlenW(const ImWchar* str)
418 {
419  size_t n = 0;
420  while (*str++)
421  n++;
422  return n;
423 }

425 static const char* ImStristr(const char* haystack, const char* needle, const char* needle_end)
426 {
427  if (!needle_end)
428  needle_end = needle + strlen(needle);
429 
430  const char un0 = (char)toupper(*needle);
431  while (*haystack)
432  {
433  if (toupper(*haystack) == un0)
434  {
435  const char* b = needle + 1;
436  for (const char* a = haystack + 1; b < needle_end; a++, b++)
437  if (toupper(*a) != toupper(*b))
438  break;
439  if (b == needle_end)
440  return haystack;
441  }
442  haystack++;
443  }
444  return NULL;
445 }
446 
447 static ImU32 crc32(const void* data, size_t data_size, ImU32 seed = 0)
448 {
449  static ImU32 crc32_lut[256] = { 0 };
450  if (!crc32_lut[1])
451  {
452  const ImU32 polynomial = 0xEDB88320;
453  for (ImU32 i = 0; i < 256; i++)
454  {
455  ImU32 crc = i;
456  for (ImU32 j = 0; j < 8; j++)
457  crc = (crc >> 1) ^ (ImU32(-int(crc & 1)) & polynomial);
458  crc32_lut[i] = crc;
459  }
460  }
461  ImU32 crc = ~seed;
462  const unsigned char* current = (const unsigned char*)data;
463  while (data_size--)
464  crc = (crc >> 8) ^ crc32_lut[(crc & 0xFF) ^ *current++];
465  return ~crc;
466 }
467 
468 static size_t ImFormatString(char* buf, size_t buf_size, const char* fmt, ...)
469 {
470  va_list args;
471  va_start(args, fmt);
472  int w = vsnprintf(buf, buf_size, fmt, args);
473  va_end(args);
474  buf[buf_size-1] = 0;
475  return (w == -1) ? buf_size : (size_t)w;
476 }
477 
478 static size_t ImFormatStringV(char* buf, size_t buf_size, const char* fmt, va_list args)
479 {
480  int w = vsnprintf(buf, buf_size, fmt, args);
481  buf[buf_size-1] = 0;
482  return (w == -1) ? buf_size : (size_t)w;
483 }

485 static ImU32 ImConvertColorFloat4ToU32(const ImVec4& in)
486 {
487  ImU32 out = ((ImU32)(ImSaturate(in.x)*255.f));
488  out |= ((ImU32)(ImSaturate(in.y)*255.f) << 8);
489  out |= ((ImU32)(ImSaturate(in.z)*255.f) << 16);
490  out |= ((ImU32)(ImSaturate(in.w)*255.f) << 24);
491  return out;
492 }

494 // Convert rgb floats ([0-1],[0-1],[0-1]) to hsv floats ([0-1],[0-1],[0-1]), from Foley & van Dam p592
495 // Optimized http://lolengine.net/blog/2013/01/13/fast-rgb-to-hsv
496 static void ImConvertColorRGBtoHSV(float r, float g, float b, float& out_h, float& out_s, float& out_v)
497 {
498  float K = 0.f;
499  if (g < b)
500  {
501  const float tmp = g; g = b; b = tmp;
502  K = -1.f;
503  }
504  if (r < g)
505  {
506  const float tmp = r; r = g; g = tmp;
507  K = -2.f / 6.f - K;
508  }
509 
510  const float chroma = r - (g < b ? g : b);
511  out_h = fabsf(K + (g - b) / (6.f * chroma + 1e-20f));
512  out_s = chroma / (r + 1e-20f);
513  out_v = r;
514 }
515 
516 // Convert hsv floats ([0-1],[0-1],[0-1]) to rgb floats ([0-1],[0-1],[0-1]), from Foley & van Dam p593
517 // also http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HSL_and_HSV
518 static void ImConvertColorHSVtoRGB(float h, float s, float v, float& out_r, float& out_g, float& out_b)
519 {
520  if (s == 0.0f)
521  {
522  // gray
523  out_r = out_g = out_b = v;
524  return;
525  }
526 
527  h = fmodf(h, 1.0f) / (60.0f/360.0f);
528  int i = (int)h;
529  float f = h - (float)i;
530  float p = v * (1.0f - s);
531  float q = v * (1.0f - s * f);
532  float t = v * (1.0f - s * (1.0f - f));
533 
534  switch (i)
535  {
536  case 0: out_r = v; out_g = t; out_b = p; break;
537  case 1: out_r = q; out_g = v; out_b = p; break;
538  case 2: out_r = p; out_g = v; out_b = t; break;
539  case 3: out_r = p; out_g = q; out_b = v; break;
540  case 4: out_r = t; out_g = p; out_b = v; break;
541  case 5: default: out_r = v; out_g = p; out_b = q; break;
542  }
543 }

553 struct ImGuiAabb // 2D axis aligned bounding-box
554 {
555  ImVec2 Min;
556  ImVec2 Max;
557 
558  ImGuiAabb() { Min = ImVec2(FLT_MAX,FLT_MAX); Max = ImVec2(-FLT_MAX,-FLT_MAX); }
559  ImGuiAabb(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) { Min = min; Max = max; }
560  ImGuiAabb(const ImVec4& v) { Min.x = v.x; Min.y = v.y; Max.x = v.z; Max.y = v.w; }
561  ImGuiAabb(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) { Min.x = x1; Min.y = y1; Max.x = x2; Max.y = y2; }
562 
563  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return Min + (Max-Min)*0.5f; }
564  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return Max-Min; }
565  float GetWidth() const { return (Max-Min).x; }
566  float GetHeight() const { return (Max-Min).y; }
567  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; }
568  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x,Min.y); }
569  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x,Max.y); }
570  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; }
571  bool Contains(ImVec2 p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x <= Max.x && p.y <= Max.y; }
572  bool Contains(const ImGuiAabb& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
573  bool Overlaps(const ImGuiAabb& r) const { return r.Min.y <= Max.y && r.Max.y >= Min.y && r.Min.x <= Max.x && r.Max.x >= Min.x; }
574  void Expand(ImVec2 sz) { Min -= sz; Max += sz; }
575  void Clip(const ImGuiAabb& clip) { Min.x = ImMax(Min.x, clip.Min.x); Min.y = ImMax(Min.y, clip.Min.y); Max.x = ImMin(Max.x, clip.Max.x); Max.y = ImMin(Max.y, clip.Max.y); }
576 };

812 // Helper: Key->value storage
813 void ImGuiStorage::Clear()
814 {
815  Data.clear();
816 }
817 
818 // std::lower_bound but without the bullshit
819 static ImVector<ImGuiStorage::Pair>::iterator LowerBound(ImVector<ImGuiStorage::Pair>& data, ImU32 key)
820 {
821  ImVector<ImGuiStorage::Pair>::iterator first = data.begin();
822  ImVector<ImGuiStorage::Pair>::iterator last = data.end();
823  int count = (int)(last - first);
824  while (count > 0)
825  {
826  int count2 = count / 2;
827  ImVector<ImGuiStorage::Pair>::iterator mid = first + count2;
828  if (mid->key < key)
829  {
830  first = ++mid;
831  count -= count2 + 1;
832  }
833  else
834  {
835  count = count2;
836  }
837  }
838  return first;
839 }
840 
841 int* ImGuiStorage::Find(ImU32 key)
842 {
843  ImVector<Pair>::iterator it = LowerBound(Data, key);
844  if (it == Data.end())
845  return NULL;
846  if (it->key != key)
847  return NULL;
848  return &it->val;
849 }
850 
851 int ImGuiStorage::GetInt(ImU32 key, int default_val)
852 {
853  int* pval = Find(key);
854  if (!pval)
855  return default_val;
856  return *pval;
857 }
858 
859 // FIXME-OPT: We are wasting time because all SetInt() are preceeded by GetInt() calls so we should have the result from lower_bound already in place.
860 // However we only use SetInt() on explicit user action (so that's maximum once a frame) so the optimisation isn't much needed.
861 void ImGuiStorage::SetInt(ImU32 key, int val)
862 {
863  ImVector<Pair>::iterator it = LowerBound(Data, key);
864  if (it != Data.end() && it->key == key)
865  {
866  it->val = val;
867  }
868  else
869  {
870  Pair pair_key;
871  pair_key.key = key;
872  pair_key.val = val;
873  Data.insert(it, pair_key);
874  }
875 }
876 
877 void ImGuiStorage::SetAllInt(int v)
878 {
879  for (size_t i = 0; i < Data.size(); i++)
880  Data[i].val = v;
881 }

885 // Helper: Parse and apply text filters. In format "aaaaa[,bbbb][,ccccc]"

892 void ImGuiTextFilter::Draw(const char* label, float width)
893 {
894  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
895  if (width < 0.0f)
896  {
897  ImVec2 label_size = ImGui::CalcTextSize(label, NULL);
898  width = ImMax(window->Pos.x + ImGui::GetWindowContentRegionMax().x - window->DC.CursorPos.x - (label_size.x + GImGui.Style.ItemSpacing.x*4), 10.0f);
899  }
900  ImGui::PushItemWidth(width);
901  ImGui::InputText(label, InputBuf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(InputBuf));
902  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
903  Build();
904 }
905 
906 void ImGuiTextFilter::TextRange::split(char separator, ImVector<TextRange>& out)
907 {
908  out.resize(0);
909  const char* wb = b;
910  const char* we = wb;
911  while (we < e)
912  {
913  if (*we == separator)
914  {
915  out.push_back(TextRange(wb, we));
916  wb = we + 1;
917  }
918  we++;
919  }
920  if (wb != we)
921  out.push_back(TextRange(wb, we));
922 }
923 
924 void ImGuiTextFilter::Build()
925 {
926  Filters.resize(0);
927  TextRange input_range(InputBuf, InputBuf+strlen(InputBuf));
928  input_range.split(',', Filters);
929 
930  CountGrep = 0;
931  for (size_t i = 0; i != Filters.size(); i++)
932  {
933  Filters[i].trim_blanks();
934  if (Filters[i].empty())
935  continue;
936  if (Filters[i].front() != '-')
937  CountGrep += 1;
938  }
939 }
940 
941 bool ImGuiTextFilter::PassFilter(const char* val) const
942 {
943  if (Filters.empty())
944  return true;
945 
946  if (val == NULL)
947  val = "";
948 
949  for (size_t i = 0; i != Filters.size(); i++)
950  {
951  const TextRange& f = Filters[i];
952  if (f.empty())
953  continue;
954  if (f.front() == '-')
955  {
956  // Subtract
957  if (ImStristr(val, f.begin()+1, f.end()) != NULL)
958  return false;
959  }
960  else
961  {
962  // Grep
963  if (ImStristr(val, f.begin(), f.end()) != NULL)
964  return true;
965  }
966  }
967 
968  // Implicit * grep
969  if (CountGrep == 0)
970  return true;
971 
972  return false;
973 }
974 
975 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
976 
977 // Helper: Text buffer for logging/accumulating text
978 void ImGuiTextBuffer::append(const char* fmt, ...)
979 {
980  va_list args;
981  va_start(args, fmt);
982  int len = vsnprintf(NULL, 0, fmt, args);
983  va_end(args);
984  if (len <= 0)
985  return;
986 
987  const size_t write_off = Buf.size();
988  if (write_off + (size_t)len >= Buf.capacity())
989  Buf.reserve(Buf.capacity() * 2);
990 
991  Buf.resize(write_off + (size_t)len);
992 
993  va_start(args, fmt);
994  ImFormatStringV(&Buf[write_off] - 1, (size_t)len+1, fmt, args);
995  va_end(args);
996 }

1031 }

1057 
1058 bool ImGuiWindow::FocusItemRegister(bool is_active)
1059 {
1060  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1061  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1062 
1063  const bool allow_keyboard_focus = window->DC.AllowKeyboardFocus.back();
1064  FocusIdxAllCounter++;
1065  if (allow_keyboard_focus)
1066  FocusIdxTabCounter++;
1067 
1068  // Process keyboard input at this point: TAB, Shift-TAB switch focus
1069  // We can always TAB out of a widget that doesn't allow tabbing in.
1070  if (FocusIdxAllRequestNext == IM_INT_MAX && FocusIdxTabRequestNext == IM_INT_MAX && is_active && ImGui::IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Tab))
1071  {
1072  // Modulo on index will be applied at the end of frame once we've got the total counter of items.
1073  FocusIdxTabRequestNext = FocusIdxTabCounter + (g.IO.KeyShift ? (allow_keyboard_focus ? -1 : 0) : +1);
1074  }
1075 
1076  if (FocusIdxAllCounter == FocusIdxAllRequestCurrent)
1077  return true;
1078 
1079  if (allow_keyboard_focus)
1080  if (FocusIdxTabCounter == FocusIdxTabRequestCurrent)
1081  return true;
1082 
1083  return false;
1084 }
1085 
1086 void ImGuiWindow::FocusItemUnregister()
1087 {
1088  FocusIdxAllCounter--;
1089  FocusIdxTabCounter--;
1090 }
1091 
1092 void ImGuiWindow::AddToRenderList()
1093 {
1094  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1095 
1096  if (!DrawList->commands.empty() && !DrawList->vtx_buffer.empty())
1097  {
1098  if (DrawList->commands.back().vtx_count == 0)
1099  DrawList->commands.pop_back();
1100  g.RenderDrawLists.push_back(DrawList);
1101  }
1102  for (size_t i = 0; i < DC.ChildWindows.size(); i++)
1103  {
1104  ImGuiWindow* child = DC.ChildWindows[i];
1105  if (child->Visible) // clipped childs may have been marked not Visible
1106  child->AddToRenderList();
1107  }
1108 }

1130 static ImGuiIniData* FindWindowSettings(const char* name)
1131 {
1132  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1133 
1134  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Settings.size(); i++)
1135  {
1136  ImGuiIniData* ini = g.Settings[i];
1137  if (ImStricmp(ini->Name, name) == 0)
1138  return ini;
1139  }
1140  ImGuiIniData* ini = (ImGuiIniData*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImGuiIniData));
1141  new(ini) ImGuiIniData();
1142  ini->Name = ImStrdup(name);
1143  ini->Collapsed = false;
1144  ini->Pos = ImVec2(FLT_MAX,FLT_MAX);
1145  ini->Size = ImVec2(0,0);
1146  g.Settings.push_back(ini);
1147  return ini;
1148 }
1149 
1150 // Zero-tolerance, poor-man .ini parsing
1151 // FIXME: Write something less rubbish
1152 static void LoadSettings()
1153 {
1154  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1155  const char* filename = g.IO.IniFilename;
1156  if (!filename)
1157  return;
1158 
1159  // Load file
1160  FILE* f;
1161  if ((f = fopen(filename, "rt")) == NULL)
1162  return;
1163  if (fseek(f, 0, SEEK_END))
1164  {
1165  fclose(f);
1166  return;
1167  }
1168  const long f_size_signed = ftell(f);
1169  if (f_size_signed == -1)
1170  {
1171  fclose(f);
1172  return;
1173  }
1174  size_t f_size = (size_t)f_size_signed;
1175  if (fseek(f, 0, SEEK_SET))
1176  {
1177  fclose(f);
1178  return;
1179  }
1180  char* f_data = (char*)ImGui::MemAlloc(f_size+1);
1181  f_size = fread(f_data, 1, f_size, f); // Text conversion alter read size so let's not be fussy about return value
1182  fclose(f);
1183  if (f_size == 0)
1184  {
1185  ImGui::MemFree(f_data);
1186  return;
1187  }
1188  f_data[f_size] = 0;
1189 
1190  ImGuiIniData* settings = NULL;
1191  const char* buf_end = f_data + f_size;
1192  for (const char* line_start = f_data; line_start < buf_end; )
1193  {
1194  const char* line_end = line_start;
1195  while (line_end < buf_end && *line_end != '\n' && *line_end != '\r')
1196  line_end++;
1197 
1198  if (line_start[0] == '[' && line_end > line_start && line_end[-1] == ']')
1199  {
1200  char name[64];
1201  ImFormatString(name, IM_ARRAYSIZE(name), "%.*s", line_end-line_start-2, line_start+1);
1202  settings = FindWindowSettings(name);
1203  }
1204  else if (settings)
1205  {
1206  float x, y;
1207  int i;
1208  if (sscanf(line_start, "Pos=%f,%f", &x, &y) == 2)
1209  settings->Pos = ImVec2(x, y);
1210  else if (sscanf(line_start, "Size=%f,%f", &x, &y) == 2)
1211  settings->Size = ImMax(ImVec2(x, y), g.Style.WindowMinSize);
1212  else if (sscanf(line_start, "Collapsed=%d", &i) == 1)
1213  settings->Collapsed = (i != 0);
1214  }
1215 
1216  line_start = line_end+1;
1217  }
1218 
1219  ImGui::MemFree(f_data);
1220 }
1221 
1222 static void SaveSettings()
1223 {
1224  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1225  const char* filename = g.IO.IniFilename;
1226  if (!filename)
1227  return;
1228 
1229  // Gather data from windows that were active during this session
1230  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1231  {
1232  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
1233  if (window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip))
1234  continue;
1235  ImGuiIniData* settings = FindWindowSettings(window->Name);
1236  settings->Pos = window->Pos;
1237  settings->Size = window->SizeFull;
1238  settings->Collapsed = window->Collapsed;
1239  }
1240 
1241  // Write .ini file
1242  // If a window wasn't opened in this session we preserve its settings
1243  FILE* f = fopen(filename, "wt");
1244  if (!f)
1245  return;
1246  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Settings.size(); i++)
1247  {
1248  const ImGuiIniData* settings = g.Settings[i];
1249  if (settings->Pos.x == FLT_MAX)
1250  continue;
1251  fprintf(f, "[%s]\n", settings->Name);
1252  fprintf(f, "Pos=%d,%d\n", (int)settings->Pos.x, (int)settings->Pos.y);
1253  fprintf(f, "Size=%d,%d\n", (int)settings->Size.x, (int)settings->Size.y);
1254  fprintf(f, "Collapsed=%d\n", settings->Collapsed);
1255  fprintf(f, "\n");
1256  }
1257 
1258  fclose(f);
1259 }
1260 
1261 static void MarkSettingsDirty()
1262 {
1263  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1264 
1265  if (g.SettingsDirtyTimer <= 0.0f)
1266  g.SettingsDirtyTimer = g.IO.IniSavingRate;
1267 }

1274 ImGuiStyle& GetStyle()

1276  return GImGui.Style;
1277 }
1278 
1279 void NewFrame()
1280 {
1281  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1282 
1283  // Check user inputs
1284  IM_ASSERT(g.IO.DeltaTime > 0.0f);
1285  IM_ASSERT(g.IO.DisplaySize.x > 0.0f && g.IO.DisplaySize.y > 0.0f);
1286  IM_ASSERT(g.IO.RenderDrawListsFn != NULL); // Must be implemented
1287  IM_ASSERT(g.IO.FontBaseScale > 0.0f);
1288 
1289  if (!g.Initialized)
1290  {
1291  // Initialize on first frame
1292  g.LogClipboard = (ImGuiTextBuffer*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImGuiTextBuffer));
1293  new(g.LogClipboard) ImGuiTextBuffer();
1294 
1295  IM_ASSERT(g.Settings.empty());
1296  LoadSettings();
1297  if (!g.IO.Font)
1298  {
1299  // Default font
1300  const void* fnt_data;
1301  unsigned int fnt_size;
1302  ImGui::GetDefaultFontData(&fnt_data, &fnt_size, NULL, NULL);
1303  g.IO.Font = (ImBitmapFont*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImBitmapFont));
1304  new(g.IO.Font) ImBitmapFont();
1305  g.IO.Font->LoadFromMemory(fnt_data, fnt_size);
1306  g.IO.FontYOffset = +1;
1307  }
1308  g.Initialized = true;
1309  }
1310  IM_ASSERT(g.IO.Font && g.IO.Font->IsLoaded()); // Font not loaded
1311 
1312  g.Time += g.IO.DeltaTime;
1313  g.FrameCount += 1;
1314  g.Tooltip[0] = '\0';
1315  g.FontSize = g.IO.FontBaseScale * g.IO.Font->GetFontSize();
1316 
1317  // Update inputs state
1318  if (g.IO.MousePos.x < 0 && g.IO.MousePos.y < 0)
1319  g.IO.MousePos = ImVec2(-9999.0f, -9999.0f);
1320  if ((g.IO.MousePos.x < 0 && g.IO.MousePos.y < 0) || (g.IO.MousePosPrev.x < 0 && g.IO.MousePosPrev.y < 0)) // if mouse just appeared or disappeared (negative coordinate) we cancel out movement in MouseDelta
1321  g.IO.MouseDelta = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
1322  else
1323  g.IO.MouseDelta = g.IO.MousePos - g.IO.MousePosPrev;
1324  g.IO.MousePosPrev = g.IO.MousePos;
1325  for (size_t i = 0; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.MouseDown); i++)
1326  {
1327  g.IO.MouseDownTime[i] = g.IO.MouseDown[i] ? (g.IO.MouseDownTime[i] < 0.0f ? 0.0f : g.IO.MouseDownTime[i] + g.IO.DeltaTime) : -1.0f;
1328  g.IO.MouseClicked[i] = (g.IO.MouseDownTime[i] == 0.0f);
1329  g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[i] = false;
1330  if (g.IO.MouseClicked[i])
1331  {
1332  if (g.Time - g.IO.MouseClickedTime[i] < g.IO.MouseDoubleClickTime)
1333  {
1334  if (ImLength(g.IO.MousePos - g.IO.MouseClickedPos[i]) < g.IO.MouseDoubleClickMaxDist)
1335  g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[i] = true;
1336  g.IO.MouseClickedTime[i] = -FLT_MAX; // so the third click isn't turned into a double-click
1337  }
1338  else
1339  {
1340  g.IO.MouseClickedTime[i] = g.Time;
1341  g.IO.MouseClickedPos[i] = g.IO.MousePos;
1342  }
1343  }
1344  }
1345  for (size_t i = 0; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.KeysDown); i++)
1346  g.IO.KeysDownTime[i] = g.IO.KeysDown[i] ? (g.IO.KeysDownTime[i] < 0.0f ? 0.0f : g.IO.KeysDownTime[i] + g.IO.DeltaTime) : -1.0f;
1347 
1348  // Clear reference to active widget if the widget isn't alive anymore
1349  g.HoveredId = 0;
1350  if (!g.ActiveIdIsAlive && g.ActiveIdPreviousFrame == g.ActiveId && g.ActiveId != 0)
1351  g.ActiveId = 0;
1352  g.ActiveIdPreviousFrame = g.ActiveId;
1353  g.ActiveIdIsAlive = false;
1354 
1355  // Delay saving settings so we don't spam disk too much
1356  if (g.SettingsDirtyTimer > 0.0f)
1357  {
1358  g.SettingsDirtyTimer -= g.IO.DeltaTime;
1359  if (g.SettingsDirtyTimer <= 0.0f)
1360  SaveSettings();
1361  }
1362 
1363  g.HoveredWindow = ImGui::FindHoveredWindow(g.IO.MousePos, false);
1364  g.HoveredWindowExcludingChilds = ImGui::FindHoveredWindow(g.IO.MousePos, true);
1365 
1366  // Are we using inputs? Tell user so they can capture/discard them.
1367  g.IO.WantCaptureMouse = (g.HoveredWindow != NULL) || (g.ActiveId != 0);
1368  g.IO.WantCaptureKeyboard = (g.ActiveId != 0);
1369 
1370  // Scale & Scrolling
1371  if (g.HoveredWindow && g.IO.MouseWheel != 0)
1372  {
1373  ImGuiWindow* window = g.HoveredWindow;
1374  if (g.IO.KeyCtrl)
1375  {
1376  if (g.IO.FontAllowUserScaling)
1377  {
1378  // Zoom / Scale window
1379  float new_font_scale = ImClamp(window->FontWindowScale + g.IO.MouseWheel * 0.10f, 0.50f, 2.50f);
1380  float scale = new_font_scale / window->FontWindowScale;
1381  window->FontWindowScale = new_font_scale;
1382 
1383  const ImVec2 offset = window->Size * (1.0f - scale) * (g.IO.MousePos - window->Pos) / window->Size;
1384  window->Pos += offset;
1385  window->PosFloat += offset;
1386  window->Size *= scale;
1387  window->SizeFull *= scale;
1388  }
1389  }
1390  else
1391  {
1392  // Scroll
1393  const int scroll_lines = (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox) ? 3 : 5;
1394  window->NextScrollY -= g.IO.MouseWheel * window->FontSize() * scroll_lines;
1395  }
1396  }
1397 
1398  // Pressing TAB activate widget focus
1399  // NB: Don't discard FocusedWindow if it isn't active, so that a window that go on/off programatically won't lose its keyboard focus.
1400  if (g.ActiveId == 0 && g.FocusedWindow != NULL && g.FocusedWindow->Visible && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Tab, false))
1401  {
1402  g.FocusedWindow->FocusIdxTabRequestNext = 0;
1403  }
1404 
1405  // Mark all windows as not visible
1406  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1407  {
1408  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
1409  window->Visible = false;
1410  window->Accessed = false;
1411  }
1412 
1413  // No window should be open at the beginning of the frame.
1414  // But in order to allow the user to call NewFrame() multiple times without calling Render(), we are doing an explicit clear.
1415  g.CurrentWindowStack.clear();
1416 
1417  // Create implicit window - we will only render it if the user has added something to it.
1418  ImGui::Begin("Debug", NULL, ImVec2(400,400));
1419 }
1420 
1421 // NB: behaviour of ImGui after Shutdown() is not tested/guaranteed at the moment. This function is merely here to free heap allocations.
1422 void Shutdown()
1423 {
1424  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1425  if (!g.Initialized)
1426  return;
1427 
1428  SaveSettings();
1429 
1430  for (size_t i = 0; i < g.Windows.size(); i++)
1431  {
1432  g.Windows[i]->~ImGuiWindow();
1433  ImGui::MemFree(g.Windows[i]);
1434  }
1435  g.Windows.clear();
1436  g.CurrentWindowStack.clear();
1437  g.RenderDrawLists.clear();
1438  g.FocusedWindow = NULL;
1439  g.HoveredWindow = NULL;
1440  g.HoveredWindowExcludingChilds = NULL;
1441  for (size_t i = 0; i < g.Settings.size(); i++)
1442  {
1443  g.Settings[i]->~ImGuiIniData();
1444  ImGui::MemFree(g.Settings[i]);
1445  }
1446  g.Settings.clear();
1447  g.ColorEditModeStorage.Clear();
1448  if (g.LogFile && g.LogFile != stdout)
1449  {
1450  fclose(g.LogFile);
1451  g.LogFile = NULL;
1452  }
1453  if (g.IO.Font)
1454  {
1455  g.IO.Font->~ImBitmapFont();
1456  ImGui::MemFree(g.IO.Font);
1457  g.IO.Font = NULL;
1458  }
1459 
1460  if (g.PrivateClipboard)
1461  {
1462  ImGui::MemFree(g.PrivateClipboard);
1463  g.PrivateClipboard = NULL;
1464  }
1465 
1466  if (g.LogClipboard)
1467  {
1468  g.LogClipboard->~ImGuiTextBuffer();
1469  ImGui::MemFree(g.LogClipboard);
1470  }
1471 
1472  g.Initialized = false;
1473 }
1474 
1475 static void AddWindowToSortedBuffer(ImGuiWindow* window, ImVector<ImGuiWindow*>& sorted_windows)
1476 {
1477  sorted_windows.push_back(window);
1478  if (window->Visible)
1479  {
1480  for (size_t i = 0; i < window->DC.ChildWindows.size(); i++)
1481  {
1482  ImGuiWindow* child = window->DC.ChildWindows[i];
1483  if (child->Visible)
1484  AddWindowToSortedBuffer(child, sorted_windows);
1485  }
1486  }
1487 }
1488 
1489 static void PushClipRect(const ImVec4& clip_rect, bool clipped = true)
1490 {
1491  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1492 
1493  ImVec4 cr = clip_rect;
1494  if (clipped && !window->ClipRectStack.empty())
1495  {
1496  // Clip to new clip rect
1497  const ImVec4 cur_cr = window->ClipRectStack.back();
1498  cr = ImVec4(ImMax(cr.x, cur_cr.x), ImMax(cr.y, cur_cr.y), ImMin(cr.z, cur_cr.z), ImMin(cr.w, cur_cr.w));
1499  }
1500 
1501  window->ClipRectStack.push_back(cr);
1502  window->DrawList->PushClipRect(cr);
1503 }
1504 
1505 static void PopClipRect()
1506 {
1507  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1508  window->ClipRectStack.pop_back();
1509  window->DrawList->PopClipRect();
1510 }
1511 
1512 void Render()
1513 {
1514  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1515  IM_ASSERT(g.Initialized); // Forgot to call ImGui::NewFrame()
1516 
1517  const bool first_render_of_the_frame = (g.FrameCountRendered != g.FrameCount);
1518  g.FrameCountRendered = g.FrameCount;
1519 
1520  if (first_render_of_the_frame)
1521  {
1522  // Hide implicit window if it hasn't been used
1523  IM_ASSERT(g.CurrentWindowStack.size() == 1); // Mismatched Begin/End
1524  if (g.CurrentWindow && !g.CurrentWindow->Accessed)
1525  g.CurrentWindow->Visible = false;
1526  ImGui::End();
1527 
1528  // Sort the window list so that all child windows are after their parent
1529  // We cannot do that on FocusWindow() because childs may not exist yet
1530  ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> sorted_windows;
1531  sorted_windows.reserve(g.Windows.size());
1532  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1533  {
1534  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
1535  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) // if a child is visible its parent will add it
1536  if (window->Visible)
1537  continue;
1538  AddWindowToSortedBuffer(window, sorted_windows);
1539  }
1540  IM_ASSERT(g.Windows.size() == sorted_windows.size()); // We done something wrong
1541  g.Windows.swap(sorted_windows);
1542 
1543  // Clear data for next frame
1544  g.IO.MouseWheel = 0;
1545  memset(g.IO.InputCharacters, 0, sizeof(g.IO.InputCharacters));
1546  }
1547 
1548  // Skip render altogether if alpha is 0.0
1549  // Note that vertex buffers have been created, so it is best practice that you don't call Begin/End in the first place.
1550  if (g.Style.Alpha > 0.0f)
1551  {
1552  // Render tooltip
1553  if (g.Tooltip[0])
1554  {
1555  // Use a dummy window to render the tooltip
1556  ImGui::BeginTooltip();
1557  ImGui::TextUnformatted(g.Tooltip);
1558  ImGui::EndTooltip();
1559  }
1560 
1561  // Gather windows to render
1562  g.RenderDrawLists.resize(0);
1563  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1564  {
1565  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
1566  if (window->Visible && (window->Flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip)) == 0)
1567  window->AddToRenderList();
1568  }
1569  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1570  {
1571  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[i];
1572  if (window->Visible && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip))
1573  window->AddToRenderList();
1574  }
1575 
1576  // Render
1577  if (!g.RenderDrawLists.empty())
1578  g.IO.RenderDrawListsFn(&g.RenderDrawLists[0], (int)g.RenderDrawLists.size());
1579  g.RenderDrawLists.resize(0);
1580  }
1581 }
1582 
1583 // Find the optional ## from which we stop displaying text.
1584 static const char* FindTextDisplayEnd(const char* text, const char* text_end = NULL)
1585 {
1586  const char* text_display_end = text;
1587  while ((!text_end || text_display_end < text_end) && *text_display_end != '\0' && (text_display_end[0] != '#' || text_display_end[1] != '#'))
1588  text_display_end++;
1589  return text_display_end;
1590 }
1591 
1592 // Log ImGui display into text output (tty or file or clipboard)
1593 static void LogText(const ImVec2& ref_pos, const char* text, const char* text_end)
1594 {
1595  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1596  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1597 
1598  if (!text_end)
1599  text_end = FindTextDisplayEnd(text, text_end);
1600 
1601  const bool log_new_line = ref_pos.y > window->DC.LogLineHeight+1;
1602  window->DC.LogLineHeight = ref_pos.y;
1603 
1604  const char* text_remaining = text;
1605  const int tree_depth = window->DC.TreeDepth;
1606  while (true)
1607  {
1608  const char* line_end = text_remaining;
1609  while (line_end < text_end)
1610  if (*line_end == '\n')
1611  break;
1612  else
1613  line_end++;
1614  if (line_end >= text_end)
1615  line_end = NULL;
1616 
1617  const bool is_first_line = (text == text_remaining);
1618  bool is_last_line = false;
1619  if (line_end == NULL)
1620  {
1621  is_last_line = true;
1622  line_end = text_end;
1623  }
1624  if (line_end != NULL && !(is_last_line && (line_end - text_remaining)==0))
1625  {
1626  const int char_count = (int)(line_end - text_remaining);
1627  if (g.LogFile)
1628  {
1629  if (log_new_line || !is_first_line)
1630  fprintf(g.LogFile, "\n%*s%.*s", tree_depth*4, "", char_count, text_remaining);
1631  else
1632  fprintf(g.LogFile, " %.*s", char_count, text_remaining);
1633  }
1634  else
1635  {
1636  if (log_new_line || !is_first_line)
1637  g.LogClipboard->append("\n%*s%.*s", tree_depth*4, "", char_count, text_remaining);
1638  else
1639  g.LogClipboard->append(" %.*s", char_count, text_remaining);
1640  }
1641  }
1642 
1643  if (is_last_line)
1644  break;
1645  text_remaining = line_end + 1;
1646  }
1647 }
1648 
1649 // Internal ImGui function to render text (called from ImGui::Text(), ImGui::TextUnformatted(), etc.)
1650 static void RenderText(ImVec2 pos, const char* text, const char* text_end, const bool hide_text_after_hash)
1651 {
1652  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1653  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1654 
1655  // Hide anything after a '##' string
1656  const char* text_display_end;
1657  if (hide_text_after_hash)
1658  {
1659  text_display_end = FindTextDisplayEnd(text, text_end);
1660  }
1661  else
1662  {
1663  if (!text_end)
1664  text_end = text + strlen(text);
1665  text_display_end = text_end;
1666  }
1667 
1668  const int text_len = (int)(text_display_end - text);
1669  //IM_ASSERT(text_len >= 0 && text_len < 10000); // Suspicious text length
1670  if (text_len > 0)
1671  {
1672  // Render
1673  window->DrawList->AddText(window->Font(), window->FontSize(), pos, window->Color(ImGuiCol_Text), text, text + text_len);
1674 
1675  // Log as text. We split text into individual lines to add the tree level padding
1676  if (g.LogEnabled)
1677  LogText(pos, text, text_display_end);
1678  }
1679 }

1681 // Render a rectangle shaped with optional rounding and borders
1682 static void RenderFrame(ImVec2 p_min, ImVec2 p_max, ImU32 fill_col, bool border, float rounding)
1683 {
1684  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1685 
1686  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(p_min, p_max, fill_col, rounding);
1687  if (border && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders))
1688  {
1689  // FIXME: I have no idea how this is working correctly but it is the best I've found that works on multiple rendering
1690  const float offset = GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset;
1691  window->DrawList->AddRect(p_min+ImVec2(1.5f-offset,1.5f-offset), p_max+ImVec2(1.0f-offset*2,1.0f-offset*2), window->Color(ImGuiCol_BorderShadow), rounding);
1692  window->DrawList->AddRect(p_min+ImVec2(0.5f-offset,0.5f-offset), p_max+ImVec2(0.0f-offset*2,0.0f-offset*2), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Border), rounding);
1693  }
1694 }
1695 
1696 // Render a triangle to denote expanded/collapsed state
1697 static void RenderCollapseTriangle(ImVec2 p_min, bool open, float scale, bool shadow)
1698 {
1699  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1700 
1701  const float h = window->FontSize() * 1.00f;
1702  const float r = h * 0.40f * scale;
1703  ImVec2 center = p_min + ImVec2(h*0.50f, h*0.50f*scale);
1704 
1705  ImVec2 a, b, c;
1706  if (open)
1707  {
1708  center.y -= r*0.25f;
1709  a = center + ImVec2(0,1)*r;
1710  b = center + ImVec2(-0.866f,-0.5f)*r;
1711  c = center + ImVec2(0.866f,-0.5f)*r;
1712  }
1713  else
1714  {
1715  a = center + ImVec2(1,0)*r;
1716  b = center + ImVec2(-0.500f,0.866f)*r;
1717  c = center + ImVec2(-0.500f,-0.866f)*r;
1718  }
1719 
1720  if (shadow && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders) != 0)
1721  window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(a+ImVec2(2,2), b+ImVec2(2,2), c+ImVec2(2,2), window->Color(ImGuiCol_BorderShadow));
1722  window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(a, b, c, window->Color(ImGuiCol_Border));
1723 }

1725 // Calculate text size. Text can be multi-line. Optionally ignore text after a ## marker.
1726 // CalcTextSize("") should return ImVec2(0.0f, GImGui.FontSize)
1727 ImVec2 CalcTextSize(const char* text, const char* text_end, const bool hide_text_after_hash)
1728 {
1729  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1730 
1731  const char* text_display_end;
1732  if (hide_text_after_hash)
1733  text_display_end = FindTextDisplayEnd(text, text_end); // Hide anything after a '##' string
1734  else
1735  text_display_end = text_end;
1736 
1737  const ImVec2 size = window->Font()->CalcTextSizeA(window->FontSize(), 0, text, text_display_end, NULL);
1738  return size;
1739 }

1741 // Find window given position, search front-to-back
1742 static ImGuiWindow* FindHoveredWindow(ImVec2 pos, bool excluding_childs)
1743 {
1744  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1745  for (int i = (int)g.Windows.size()-1; i >= 0; i--)
1746  {
1747  ImGuiWindow* window = g.Windows[(size_t)i];
1748  if (!window->Visible)
1749  continue;
1750  if (excluding_childs && (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) != 0)
1751  continue;
1752  ImGuiAabb bb(window->Pos - g.Style.TouchExtraPadding, window->Pos+window->Size + g.Style.TouchExtraPadding);
1753  if (bb.Contains(pos))
1754  return window;
1755  }
1756  return NULL;
1757 }

1759 // Test if mouse cursor is hovering given aabb
1760 // NB- Box is clipped by our current clip setting
1761 // NB- Expand the aabb to be generous on unprecise inputs systems (g.Style.TouchExtraPadding)
1762 static bool IsMouseHoveringBox(const ImGuiAabb& box)
1763 {
1764  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1765  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1766 
1767  // Clip
1768  ImGuiAabb box_clipped = box;
1769  if (!window->ClipRectStack.empty())
1770  {
1771  const ImVec4 clip_rect = window->ClipRectStack.back();
1772  box_clipped.Clip(ImGuiAabb(ImVec2(clip_rect.x, clip_rect.y), ImVec2(clip_rect.z, clip_rect.w)));
1773  }
1774 
1775  // Expand for touch input
1776  const ImGuiAabb box_for_touch(box_clipped.Min - g.Style.TouchExtraPadding, box_clipped.Max + g.Style.TouchExtraPadding);
1777  return box_for_touch.Contains(g.IO.MousePos);
1778 }
1779 
1780 bool IsMouseHoveringBox(const ImVec2& box_min, const ImVec2& box_max)
1781 {
1782  return IsMouseHoveringBox(ImGuiAabb(box_min, box_max));
1783 }

1809 
1810 bool IsKeyPressed(int key_index, bool repeat)
1811 {
1812  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1813  IM_ASSERT(key_index >= 0 && key_index < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.KeysDown));
1814  const float t = g.IO.KeysDownTime[key_index];
1815  if (t == 0.0f)
1816  return true;
1817 
1818  // FIXME: Repeat rate should be provided elsewhere?
1819  const float KEY_REPEAT_DELAY = 0.250f;
1820  const float KEY_REPEAT_RATE = 0.020f;
1821  if (repeat && t > KEY_REPEAT_DELAY)
1822  if ((fmodf(t - KEY_REPEAT_DELAY, KEY_REPEAT_RATE) > KEY_REPEAT_RATE*0.5f) != (fmodf(t - KEY_REPEAT_DELAY - g.IO.DeltaTime, KEY_REPEAT_RATE) > KEY_REPEAT_RATE*0.5f))
1823  return true;
1824 
1825  return false;
1826 }
1827 
1828 bool IsMouseClicked(int button, bool repeat)
1829 {
1830  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1831  IM_ASSERT(button >= 0 && button < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.MouseDown));
1832  const float t = g.IO.MouseDownTime[button];
1833  if (t == 0.0f)
1834  return true;
1835 
1836  // FIXME: Repeat rate should be provided elsewhere?
1837  const float MOUSE_REPEAT_DELAY = 0.250f;
1838  const float MOUSE_REPEAT_RATE = 0.020f;
1839  if (repeat && t > MOUSE_REPEAT_DELAY)
1840  if ((fmodf(t - MOUSE_REPEAT_DELAY, MOUSE_REPEAT_RATE) > MOUSE_REPEAT_RATE*0.5f) != (fmodf(t - MOUSE_REPEAT_DELAY - g.IO.DeltaTime, MOUSE_REPEAT_RATE) > MOUSE_REPEAT_RATE*0.5f))
1841  return true;
1842 
1843  return false;
1844 }

1908 static ImGuiWindow* FindWindow(const char* name)
1909 {

1911  for (size_t i = 0; i != g.Windows.size(); i++)
1912  if (strcmp(g.Windows[i]->Name, name) == 0)
1913  return g.Windows[i];
1914  return NULL;
1915 }

1928 void BeginChild(const char* str_id, ImVec2 size, bool border, ImGuiWindowFlags extra_flags)
1929 {
1930  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1931  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1932 
1933  ImGuiWindowFlags flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove|ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize|ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow;
1934 
1935  const ImVec2 content_max = window->Pos + ImGui::GetWindowContentRegionMax();
1936  const ImVec2 cursor_pos = window->Pos + ImGui::GetCursorPos();
1937  if (size.x <= 0.0f)
1938  {
1939  size.x = ImMax(content_max.x - cursor_pos.x, g.Style.WindowMinSize.x);
1940  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitX;
1941  }
1942  if (size.y <= 0.0f)
1943  {
1944  size.y = ImMax(content_max.y - cursor_pos.y, g.Style.WindowMinSize.y);
1945  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitY;
1946  }
1947  if (border)
1948  flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders;
1949  flags |= extra_flags;
1950 
1951  char title[256];
1952  ImFormatString(title, IM_ARRAYSIZE(title), "%s.%s", window->Name, str_id);
1953 
1954  const float alpha = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox) ? 1.0f : 0.0f;
1955  ImGui::Begin(title, NULL, size, alpha, flags);
1956 
1957  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders))
1958  g.CurrentWindow->Flags &= ~ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders;
1959 }
1960 
1961 void EndChild()
1962 {
1963  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
1964 
1965  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox)
1966  {
1967  ImGui::End();
1968  }
1969  else
1970  {
1971  // When using auto-filling child window, we don't provide the width/height to ItemSize so that it doesn't feed back into automatic size-fitting.
1972  ImVec2 sz = ImGui::GetWindowSize();
1973  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitX)
1974  sz.x = 0;
1975  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindowAutoFitY)
1976  sz.y = 0;
1977 
1978  ImGui::End();
1979  ImGui::ItemSize(sz);
1980  }
1981 }
1982 
1983 // Push a new ImGui window to add widgets to. This can be called multiple times with the same window to append contents
1984 bool Begin(const char* name, bool* open, ImVec2 size, float fill_alpha, ImGuiWindowFlags flags)
1985 {
1986  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
1987  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
1988 
1989  ImGuiWindow* window = FindWindow(name);
1990  if (!window)
1991  {
1992  // Create window the first time, and load settings
1993  if (flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip))
1994  {
1995  // Tooltip and child windows don't store settings
1996  window = (ImGuiWindow*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImGuiWindow));
1997  new(window) ImGuiWindow(name, ImVec2(0,0), size);
1998  }
1999  else
2000  {
2001  ImGuiIniData* settings = FindWindowSettings(name);
2002  if (settings && ImLength(settings->Size) > 0.0f && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))// && ImLengthsize) == 0.0f)
2003  size = settings->Size;
2004 
2005  window = (ImGuiWindow*)ImGui::MemAlloc(sizeof(ImGuiWindow));
2006  new(window) ImGuiWindow(name, g.NewWindowDefaultPos, size);
2007 
2008  if (settings->Pos.x != FLT_MAX)
2009  {
2010  window->PosFloat = settings->Pos;
2011  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
2012  window->Collapsed = settings->Collapsed;
2013  }
2014  }
2015  g.Windows.push_back(window);
2016  }
2017  window->Flags = (ImGuiWindowFlags)flags;
2018 
2019  g.CurrentWindowStack.push_back(window);
2020  g.CurrentWindow = window;
2021 
2022  // Default alpha
2023  if (fill_alpha < 0.0f)
2024  fill_alpha = style.WindowFillAlphaDefault;
2025 
2026  // When reusing window again multiple times a frame, just append content (don't need to setup again)
2027  const int current_frame = ImGui::GetFrameCount();
2028  const bool first_begin_of_the_frame = (window->LastFrameDrawn != current_frame);
2029  if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
2030  {
2031  window->DrawList->Clear();
2032  window->Visible = true;
2033 
2034  // New windows appears in front
2035  if (window->LastFrameDrawn < current_frame - 1)
2036  {
2037  ImGui::FocusWindow(window);
2038  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0)
2039  {
2040  // Hide for 1 frame while resizing
2041  window->AutoFitFrames = 2;
2042  window->Visible = false;
2043  }
2044  }
2045 
2046  window->LastFrameDrawn = current_frame;
2047  window->ClipRectStack.resize(0);
2048 
2049  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
2050  {
2051  ImGuiWindow* parent_window = g.CurrentWindowStack[g.CurrentWindowStack.size()-2];
2052  parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.push_back(window);
2053  window->Pos = window->PosFloat = parent_window->DC.CursorPos;
2054  window->SizeFull = size;
2055  }
2056 
2057  // Outer clipping rectangle
2058  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox))
2059  ImGui::PushClipRect(g.CurrentWindowStack[g.CurrentWindowStack.size()-2]->ClipRectStack.back());
2060  else
2061  ImGui::PushClipRect(ImVec4(0.0f, 0.0f, g.IO.DisplaySize.x, g.IO.DisplaySize.y));
2062 
2063  // Seed ID stack with our window pointer
2064  window->IDStack.resize(0);
2065  ImGui::PushID(window);
2066 
2067  // Move window (at the beginning of the frame to avoid lag)
2068  const ImGuiID move_id = window->GetID("#MOVE");
2069  RegisterAliveId(move_id);
2070  if (g.ActiveId == move_id)
2071  {
2072  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
2073  {
2074  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMove))
2075  {
2076  window->PosFloat += g.IO.MouseDelta;
2077  MarkSettingsDirty();
2078  }
2079  ImGui::FocusWindow(window);
2080  }
2081  else
2082  {
2083  g.ActiveId = 0;
2084  }
2085  }
2086 
2087  // Tooltips always follow mouse
2088  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0)
2089  {
2090  window->PosFloat = g.IO.MousePos + ImVec2(32,16) - g.Style.FramePadding*2;
2091  }
2092 
2093  // Clamp into view
2094  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow))
2095  {
2096  const ImVec2 pad = ImVec2(window->FontSize()*2.0f, window->FontSize()*2.0f);
2097  window->PosFloat = ImMax(window->PosFloat + window->Size, pad) - window->Size;
2098  window->PosFloat = ImMin(window->PosFloat, ImVec2(g.IO.DisplaySize.x, g.IO.DisplaySize.y) - pad);
2099  window->SizeFull = ImMax(window->SizeFull, pad);
2100  }
2101  window->Pos = ImVec2((float)(int)window->PosFloat.x, (float)(int)window->PosFloat.y);
2102 
2103  // Default item width
2104  if (window->Size.x > 0.0f && !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip))
2105  window->ItemWidthDefault = (float)(int)(window->Size.x * 0.65f);
2106  else
2107  window->ItemWidthDefault = 200.0f;
2108 
2109  // Prepare for focus requests
2110  if (window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext == IM_INT_MAX || window->FocusIdxAllCounter == -1)
2111  window->FocusIdxAllRequestCurrent = IM_INT_MAX;
2112  else
2113  window->FocusIdxAllRequestCurrent = (window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext + (window->FocusIdxAllCounter+1)) % (window->FocusIdxAllCounter+1);
2114  if (window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext == IM_INT_MAX || window->FocusIdxTabCounter == -1)
2115  window->FocusIdxTabRequestCurrent = IM_INT_MAX;
2116  else
2117  window->FocusIdxTabRequestCurrent = (window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext + (window->FocusIdxTabCounter+1)) % (window->FocusIdxTabCounter+1);
2118  window->FocusIdxAllCounter = window->FocusIdxTabCounter = -1;
2119  window->FocusIdxAllRequestNext = window->FocusIdxTabRequestNext = IM_INT_MAX;
2120 
2121  ImGuiAabb title_bar_aabb = window->TitleBarAabb();
2122 
2123  // Apply and ImClamp scrolling
2124  window->ScrollY = window->NextScrollY;
2125  window->ScrollY = ImMax(window->ScrollY, 0.0f);
2126  if (!window->Collapsed && !window->SkipItems)
2127  window->ScrollY = ImMin(window->ScrollY, ImMax(0.0f, (float)window->SizeContentsFit.y - window->SizeFull.y));
2128  window->NextScrollY = window->ScrollY;
2129 
2130  // At this point we don't have a clipping rectangle setup yet, so we can test and draw in title bar
2131  // Collapse window by double-clicking on title bar
2132  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
2133  {
2134  if (g.HoveredWindow == window && IsMouseHoveringBox(title_bar_aabb) && g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0])
2135  {
2136  window->Collapsed = !window->Collapsed;
2137  MarkSettingsDirty();
2138  ImGui::FocusWindow(window);
2139  }
2140  }
2141  else
2142  {
2143  window->Collapsed = false;
2144  }
2145 
2146  if (window->Collapsed)
2147  {
2148  // Draw title bar only
2149  window->Size = title_bar_aabb.GetSize();
2150  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(title_bar_aabb.GetTL(), title_bar_aabb.GetBR(), window->Color(ImGuiCol_TitleBgCollapsed), g.Style.WindowRounding);
2151  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders)
2152  {
2153  window->DrawList->AddRect(title_bar_aabb.GetTL()+ImVec2(1,1), title_bar_aabb.GetBR()+ImVec2(1,1), window->Color(ImGuiCol_BorderShadow), g.Style.WindowRounding);
2154  window->DrawList->AddRect(title_bar_aabb.GetTL(), title_bar_aabb.GetBR(), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Border), g.Style.WindowRounding);
2155  }
2156  }
2157  else
2158  {
2159  window->Size = window->SizeFull;
2160 
2161  ImU32 resize_col = 0;
2162  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0)
2163  {
2164  // Tooltip always resize
2165  if (window->AutoFitFrames > 0)
2166  {
2167  window->SizeFull = window->SizeContentsFit + g.Style.WindowPadding - ImVec2(0.0f, g.Style.ItemSpacing.y);
2168  }
2169  }
2170  else if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))
2171  {
2172  // Draw resize grip
2173  const ImGuiAabb resize_aabb(window->Aabb().GetBR()-ImVec2(18,18), window->Aabb().GetBR());
2174  const ImGuiID resize_id = window->GetID("#RESIZE");
2175  bool hovered, held;
2176  ButtonBehaviour(resize_aabb, resize_id, &hovered, &held, true);
2177  resize_col = window->Color(held ? ImGuiCol_ResizeGripActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ResizeGripHovered : ImGuiCol_ResizeGrip);
2178 
2179  ImVec2 size_auto_fit = ImClamp(window->SizeContentsFit + style.AutoFitPadding, style.WindowMinSize, g.IO.DisplaySize - style.AutoFitPadding);
2180  if (window->AutoFitFrames > 0)
2181  {
2182  // Auto-fit only grows during the first few frames
2183  window->SizeFull = ImMax(window->SizeFull, size_auto_fit);
2184  MarkSettingsDirty();
2185  }
2186  else if (g.HoveredWindow == window && held && g.IO.MouseDoubleClicked[0])
2187  {
2188  // Manual auto-fit
2189  window->SizeFull = size_auto_fit;
2190  window->Size = window->SizeFull;
2191  MarkSettingsDirty();
2192  }
2193  else if (held)
2194  {
2195  // Resize
2196  window->SizeFull = ImMax(window->SizeFull + g.IO.MouseDelta, style.WindowMinSize);
2197  window->Size = window->SizeFull;
2198  MarkSettingsDirty();
2199  }
2200 
2201  // Update aabb immediately so that the rendering below isn't one frame late
2202  title_bar_aabb = window->TitleBarAabb();
2203  }
2204 
2205  // Title bar + Window box
2206  if (fill_alpha > 0.0f)
2207  {
2208  if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox) != 0)
2209  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(window->Pos, window->Pos+window->Size, window->Color(ImGuiCol_ComboBg, fill_alpha), 0);
2210  else
2211  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(window->Pos, window->Pos+window->Size, window->Color(ImGuiCol_WindowBg, fill_alpha), g.Style.WindowRounding);
2212  }
2213 
2214  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
2215  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(title_bar_aabb.GetTL(), title_bar_aabb.GetBR(), window->Color(ImGuiCol_TitleBg), g.Style.WindowRounding, 1|2);
2216 
2217  // Borders
2218  if (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders)
2219  {
2220  const float rounding = (window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox) ? 0.0f : g.Style.WindowRounding;
2221  window->DrawList->AddRect(window->Pos+ImVec2(1,1), window->Pos+window->Size+ImVec2(1,1), window->Color(ImGuiCol_BorderShadow), rounding);
2222  window->DrawList->AddRect(window->Pos, window->Pos+window->Size, window->Color(ImGuiCol_Border), rounding);
2223  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
2224  window->DrawList->AddLine(title_bar_aabb.GetBL(), title_bar_aabb.GetBR(), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Border));
2225  }
2226 
2227  // Scrollbar
2228  window->ScrollbarY = (window->SizeContentsFit.y > window->Size.y) && !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar);
2229  if (window->ScrollbarY)
2230  {
2231  ImGuiAabb scrollbar_bb(window->Aabb().Max.x - style.ScrollBarWidth, title_bar_aabb.Max.y+1, window->Aabb().Max.x, window->Aabb().Max.y-1);
2232  //window->DrawList->AddLine(scrollbar_bb.GetTL(), scrollbar_bb.GetBL(), g.Colors[ImGuiCol_Border]);
2233  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(scrollbar_bb.Min, scrollbar_bb.Max, window->Color(ImGuiCol_ScrollbarBg));
2234  scrollbar_bb.Expand(ImVec2(-3,-3));
2235 
2236  const float grab_size_y_norm = ImSaturate(window->Size.y / ImMax(window->SizeContentsFit.y, window->Size.y));
2237  const float grab_size_y = scrollbar_bb.GetHeight() * grab_size_y_norm;
2238 
2239  // Handle input right away (none of the code above is relying on scrolling position)
2240  bool held = false;
2241  bool hovered = false;
2242  if (grab_size_y_norm < 1.0f)
2243  {
2244  const ImGuiID scrollbar_id = window->GetID("#SCROLLY");
2245  ButtonBehaviour(scrollbar_bb, scrollbar_id, &hovered, &held, true);
2246  if (held)
2247  {
2248  g.HoveredId = scrollbar_id;
2249  const float pos_y_norm = ImSaturate((g.IO.MousePos.y - (scrollbar_bb.Min.y + grab_size_y*0.5f)) / (scrollbar_bb.GetHeight() - grab_size_y)) * (1.0f - grab_size_y_norm);
2250  window->ScrollY = pos_y_norm * window->SizeContentsFit.y;
2251  window->NextScrollY = window->ScrollY;
2252  }
2253  }
2254 
2255  // Normalized height of the grab
2256  const float pos_y_norm = ImSaturate(window->ScrollY / ImMax(0.0f, window->SizeContentsFit.y));
2257  const ImU32 grab_col = window->Color(held ? ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabHovered : ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrab);
2258  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(
2259  ImVec2(scrollbar_bb.Min.x, ImLerp(scrollbar_bb.Min.y, scrollbar_bb.Max.y, pos_y_norm)),
2260  ImVec2(scrollbar_bb.Max.x, ImLerp(scrollbar_bb.Min.y, scrollbar_bb.Max.y, pos_y_norm + grab_size_y_norm)), grab_col);
2261  }
2262 
2263  // Render resize grip
2264  // (after the input handling so we don't have a frame of latency)
2265  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoResize))
2266  {
2267  const float r = style.WindowRounding;
2268  const ImVec2 br = window->Aabb().GetBR();
2269  if (r == 0.0f)
2270  {
2271  window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(br, br-ImVec2(0,14), br-ImVec2(14,0), resize_col);
2272  }
2273  else
2274  {
2275  // FIXME: We should draw 4 triangles and decide on a size that's not dependant on the rounding size (previously used 18)
2276  window->DrawList->AddArc(br - ImVec2(r,r), r, resize_col, 6, 9, true);
2277  window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(br+ImVec2(0,-2*r),br+ImVec2(0,-r),br+ImVec2(-r,-r), resize_col);
2278  window->DrawList->AddTriangleFilled(br+ImVec2(-r,-r), br+ImVec2(-r,0),br+ImVec2(-2*r,0), resize_col);
2279  }
2280  }
2281  }
2282 
2283  // Setup drawing context
2284  window->DC.ColumnStartX = window->WindowPadding().x;
2285  window->DC.CursorStartPos = window->Pos + ImVec2(window->DC.ColumnStartX, window->TitleBarHeight() + window->WindowPadding().y) - ImVec2(0.0f, window->ScrollY);
2286  window->DC.CursorPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
2287  window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine = window->DC.CursorPos;
2288  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = window->DC.PrevLineHeight = 0.0f;
2289  window->DC.LogLineHeight = window->DC.CursorPos.y - 9999.0f;
2290  window->DC.ChildWindows.resize(0);
2291  window->DC.ItemWidth.resize(0);
2292  window->DC.ItemWidth.push_back(window->ItemWidthDefault);
2293  window->DC.AllowKeyboardFocus.resize(0);
2294  window->DC.AllowKeyboardFocus.push_back(true);
2295  window->DC.ColorModifiers.resize(0);
2296  window->DC.ColorEditMode = ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelect;
2297  window->DC.ColumnCurrent = 0;
2298  window->DC.ColumnsCount = 1;
2299  window->DC.TreeDepth = 0;
2300  window->DC.StateStorage = &window->StateStorage;
2301  window->DC.OpenNextNode = -1;
2302 
2303  // Reset contents size for auto-fitting
2304  window->SizeContentsFit = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
2305  if (window->AutoFitFrames > 0)
2306  window->AutoFitFrames--;
2307 
2308  // Title bar
2309  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
2310  {
2311  RenderCollapseTriangle(window->Pos + style.FramePadding, !window->Collapsed, 1.0f, true);
2312  if (open)
2313  ImGui::CloseWindowButton(open);
2314 
2315  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(name);
2316  const ImVec2 text_min = window->Pos + style.FramePadding + ImVec2(window->FontSize() + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, 0.0f);
2317  const ImVec2 text_max = window->Pos + ImVec2(window->Size.x - (open ? (title_bar_aabb.GetHeight()-3) : style.FramePadding.x), style.FramePadding.y + text_size.y);
2318  const bool clip_title = text_size.x > (text_max.x - text_min.x); // only push a clip rectangle if we need to, because it may turn into a separate draw call
2319  if (clip_title)
2320  ImGui::PushClipRect(ImVec4(text_min.x, text_min.y, text_max.x, text_max.y));
2321  RenderText(text_min, name);
2322  if (clip_title)
2323  ImGui::PopClipRect();
2324  }
2325  }
2326  else
2327  {
2328  // Outer clipping rectangle
2329  if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox))
2330  {
2331  ImGuiWindow* parent_window = g.CurrentWindowStack[g.CurrentWindowStack.size()-2];
2332  ImGui::PushClipRect(parent_window->ClipRectStack.back());
2333  }
2334  else
2335  {
2336  ImGui::PushClipRect(ImVec4(0.0f, 0.0f, g.IO.DisplaySize.x, g.IO.DisplaySize.y));
2337  }
2338  }
2339 
2340  // Inner clipping rectangle
2341  // We set this up after processing the resize grip so that our clip rectangle doesn't lag by a frame
2342  const ImGuiAabb title_bar_aabb = window->TitleBarAabb();
2343  ImVec4 clip_rect(title_bar_aabb.Min.x+0.5f+window->WindowPadding().x*0.5f, title_bar_aabb.Max.y+0.5f, window->Aabb().Max.x+0.5f-window->WindowPadding().x*0.5f, window->Aabb().Max.y-1.5f);
2344  if (window->ScrollbarY)
2345  clip_rect.z -= g.Style.ScrollBarWidth;
2346  ImGui::PushClipRect(clip_rect);
2347 
2348  // Clear 'accessed' flag last thing
2349  if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
2350  window->Accessed = false;
2351 
2352  // Child window can be out of sight and have "negative" clip windows.
2353  // Mark them as collapsed so commands are skipped earlier (we can't manually collapse because they have no title bar).
2354  if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
2355  {
2356  IM_ASSERT((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) != 0);
2357  const ImVec4 clip_rect = window->ClipRectStack.back();
2358  window->Collapsed = (clip_rect.x >= clip_rect.z || clip_rect.y >= clip_rect.w);
2359 
2360  // We also hide the window from rendering because we've already added its border to the command list.
2361  // (we could perform the check earlier in the function but it is simplier at this point)
2362  if (window->Collapsed)
2363  window->Visible = false;
2364  }
2365  if (g.Style.Alpha <= 0.0f)
2366  window->Visible = false;
2367 
2368  // Return false if we don't intend to display anything to allow user to perform an early out optimisation
2369  window->SkipItems = window->Collapsed || (!window->Visible && window->AutoFitFrames == 0);
2370  return !window->SkipItems;
2371 }
2372 
2373 void End()
2374 {
2375  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
2376  ImGuiWindow* window = g.CurrentWindow;
2377 
2378  ImGui::Columns(1, "#CloseColumns");
2379  ImGui::PopClipRect(); // inner window clip rectangle
2380  ImGui::PopClipRect(); // outer window clip rectangle
2381 
2382  // Select window for move/focus when we're done with all our widgets (we only consider non-childs windows here)
2383  const ImGuiAabb bb(window->Pos, window->Pos+window->Size);
2384  if (g.ActiveId == 0 && g.HoveredId == 0 && g.HoveredWindowExcludingChilds == window && IsMouseHoveringBox(bb) && g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
2385  g.ActiveId = window->GetID("#MOVE");
2386 
2387  // Stop logging
2388  if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)) // FIXME: add more options for scope of logging
2389  {
2390  g.LogEnabled = false;
2391  if (g.LogFile != NULL)
2392  {
2393  fprintf(g.LogFile, "\n");
2394  if (g.LogFile == stdout)
2395  fflush(g.LogFile);
2396  else
2397  fclose(g.LogFile);
2398  g.LogFile = NULL;
2399  }
2400  if (g.LogClipboard->size() > 1)
2401  {
2402  g.LogClipboard->append("\n");
2403  if (g.IO.SetClipboardTextFn)
2404  g.IO.SetClipboardTextFn(g.LogClipboard->begin());
2405  g.LogClipboard->clear();
2406  }
2407  }
2408 
2409  // Pop
2410  g.CurrentWindowStack.pop_back();
2411  g.CurrentWindow = g.CurrentWindowStack.empty() ? NULL : g.CurrentWindowStack.back();
2412 }
2413 
2414 // Moving window to front
2415 static void FocusWindow(ImGuiWindow* window)
2416 {
2417  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
2418  g.FocusedWindow = window;
2419 
2420  for (size_t i = 0; i < g.Windows.size(); i++)
2421  if (g.Windows[i] == window)
2422  {
2423  g.Windows.erase(g.Windows.begin() + i);
2424  break;
2425  }
2426  g.Windows.push_back(window);
2427 }

2482 const char* GetStyleColorName(ImGuiCol idx)
2483 {
2484  // Create switch-case from enum with regexp: ImGuiCol_{.*}, --> case ImGuiCol_\1: return "\1";
2485  switch (idx)
2486  {
2487  case ImGuiCol_Text: return "Text";
2488  case ImGuiCol_WindowBg: return "WindowBg";
2489  case ImGuiCol_Border: return "Border";
2490  case ImGuiCol_BorderShadow: return "BorderShadow";
2491  case ImGuiCol_FrameBg: return "FrameBg";
2492  case ImGuiCol_TitleBg: return "TitleBg";
2493  case ImGuiCol_TitleBgCollapsed: return "TitleBgCollapsed";
2494  case ImGuiCol_ScrollbarBg: return "ScrollbarBg";
2495  case ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrab: return "ScrollbarGrab";
2496  case ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabHovered: return "ScrollbarGrabHovered";
2497  case ImGuiCol_ScrollbarGrabActive: return "ScrollbarGrabActive";
2498  case ImGuiCol_ComboBg: return "ComboBg";
2499  case ImGuiCol_CheckHovered: return "CheckHovered";
2500  case ImGuiCol_CheckActive: return "CheckActive";
2501  case ImGuiCol_SliderGrab: return "SliderGrab";
2502  case ImGuiCol_SliderGrabActive: return "SliderGrabActive";
2503  case ImGuiCol_Button: return "Button";
2504  case ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered: return "ButtonHovered";
2505  case ImGuiCol_ButtonActive: return "ButtonActive";
2506  case ImGuiCol_Header: return "Header";
2507  case ImGuiCol_HeaderHovered: return "HeaderHovered";
2508  case ImGuiCol_HeaderActive: return "HeaderActive";
2509  case ImGuiCol_Column: return "Column";
2510  case ImGuiCol_ColumnHovered: return "ColumnHovered";
2511  case ImGuiCol_ColumnActive: return "ColumnActive";
2512  case ImGuiCol_ResizeGrip: return "ResizeGrip";
2513  case ImGuiCol_ResizeGripHovered: return "ResizeGripHovered";
2514  case ImGuiCol_ResizeGripActive: return "ResizeGripActive";
2515  case ImGuiCol_CloseButton: return "CloseButton";
2516  case ImGuiCol_CloseButtonHovered: return "CloseButtonHovered";
2517  case ImGuiCol_CloseButtonActive: return "CloseButtonActive";
2518  case ImGuiCol_PlotLines: return "PlotLines";
2519  case ImGuiCol_PlotLinesHovered: return "PlotLinesHovered";
2520  case ImGuiCol_PlotHistogram: return "PlotHistogram";
2521  case ImGuiCol_PlotHistogramHovered: return "PlotHistogramHovered";
2522  case ImGuiCol_TextSelectedBg: return "TextSelectedBg";
2523  case ImGuiCol_TooltipBg: return "TooltipBg";
2524  }
2525  IM_ASSERT(0);
2526  return "Unknown";
2527 }

2693 
2694 void TextUnformatted(const char* text, const char* text_end)
2695 {
2696  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
2697  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
2698  if (window->SkipItems)
2699  return;
2700 
2701  IM_ASSERT(text != NULL);
2702  const char* text_begin = text;
2703  if (text_end == NULL)
2704  text_end = text + strlen(text);
2705 
2706  if (text_end - text > 2000)
2707  {
2708  // Long text!
2709  // Perform manual coarse clipping to optimize for long multi-line text
2710  // From this point we will only compute the width of lines that are visible.
2711  const char* line = text;
2712  const float line_height = ImGui::GetTextLineHeight();
2713  const ImVec2 start_pos = window->DC.CursorPos;
2714  const ImVec4 clip_rect = window->ClipRectStack.back();
2715  ImVec2 text_size(0,0);
2716 
2717  if (start_pos.y <= clip_rect.w)
2718  {
2719  ImVec2 pos = start_pos;
2720 
2721  // Lines to skip (can't skip when logging text)
2722  if (!g.LogEnabled)
2723  {
2724  int lines_skippable = (int)((clip_rect.y - start_pos.y) / line_height) - 1;
2725  if (lines_skippable > 0)
2726  {
2727  int lines_skipped = 0;
2728  while (line < text_end && lines_skipped <= lines_skippable)
2729  {
2730  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
2731  line = line_end + 1;
2732  lines_skipped++;
2733  }
2734  pos.y += lines_skipped * line_height;
2735  }
2736  }
2737 
2738  // Lines to render
2739  if (line < text_end)
2740  {
2741  ImGuiAabb line_box(pos, pos + ImVec2(ImGui::GetWindowWidth(), line_height));
2742  while (line < text_end)
2743  {
2744  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
2745  if (ImGui::IsClipped(line_box))
2746  break;
2747 
2748  const ImVec2 line_size = CalcTextSize(line, line_end, false);
2749  text_size.x = ImMax(text_size.x, line_size.x);
2750  RenderText(pos, line, line_end, false);
2751  if (!line_end)
2752  line_end = text_end;
2753  line = line_end + 1;
2754  line_box.Min.y += line_height;
2755  line_box.Max.y += line_height;
2756  pos.y += line_height;
2757  }
2758 
2759  // Count remaining lines
2760  int lines_skipped = 0;
2761  while (line < text_end)
2762  {
2763  const char* line_end = strchr(line, '\n');
2764  if (!line_end)
2765  line_end = text_end;
2766  line = line_end + 1;
2767  lines_skipped++;
2768  }
2769  pos.y += lines_skipped * line_height;
2770  }
2771 
2772  text_size.y += (pos - start_pos).y;
2773  }
2774  const ImGuiAabb bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + text_size);
2775  ItemSize(bb);
2776  ClipAdvance(bb);
2777  }
2778  else
2779  {
2780  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(text_begin, text_end, false);
2781  ImGuiAabb bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + text_size);
2782  ItemSize(bb.GetSize(), &bb.Min);
2783 
2784  if (ClipAdvance(bb))
2785  return;
2786 
2787  // Render
2788  // We don't hide text after ## in this end-user function.
2789  RenderText(bb.Min, text_begin, text_end, false);
2790  }
2791 }

2802  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);

2840 static bool ButtonBehaviour(const ImGuiAabb& bb, const ImGuiID& id, bool* out_hovered, bool* out_held, bool allow_key_modifiers, bool repeat)
2841 {
2842  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
2843  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
2844 
2845  const bool hovered = (g.HoveredWindow == window) && (g.HoveredId == 0) && IsMouseHoveringBox(bb);
2846  bool pressed = false;
2847  if (hovered)
2848  {
2849  g.HoveredId = id;
2850  if (allow_key_modifiers || (!g.IO.KeyCtrl && !g.IO.KeyShift))
2851  {
2852  if (g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
2853  {
2854  g.ActiveId = id;
2855  }
2856  else if (repeat && g.ActiveId && ImGui::IsMouseClicked(0, true))
2857  {
2858  pressed = true;
2859  }
2860  }
2861  }
2862 
2863  bool held = false;
2864  if (g.ActiveId == id)
2865  {
2866  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
2867  {
2868  held = true;
2869  }
2870  else
2871  {
2872  if (hovered)
2873  pressed = true;
2874  g.ActiveId = 0;
2875  }
2876  }
2877 
2878  if (out_hovered) *out_hovered = hovered;
2879  if (out_held) *out_held = held;
2880 
2881  return pressed;
2882 }
2883 
2884 bool Button(const char* label, ImVec2 size, bool repeat_when_held)
2885 {
2886  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
2887  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
2888  if (window->SkipItems)
2889  return false;
2890 
2891  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
2892  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
2893 
2894  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
2895  if (size.x == 0.0f)
2896  size.x = text_size.x;
2897  if (size.y == 0.0f)
2898  size.y = text_size.y;
2899 
2900  const ImGuiAabb bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos+size + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
2901  ItemSize(bb);
2902 
2903  if (ClipAdvance(bb))
2904  return false;
2905 
2906  bool hovered, held;
2907  bool pressed = ButtonBehaviour(bb, id, &hovered, &held, true, repeat_when_held);
2908 
2909  // Render
2910  const ImU32 col = window->Color((hovered && held) ? ImGuiCol_ButtonActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_Button);
2911  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col);
2912 
2913  if (size.x < text_size.x || size.y < text_size.y)
2914  PushClipRect(ImVec4(bb.Min.x+style.FramePadding.x, bb.Min.y+style.FramePadding.y, bb.Max.x, bb.Max.y-style.FramePadding.y)); // Allow extra to draw over the horizontal padding to make it visible that text doesn't fit
2915  const ImVec2 off = ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, size.x - text_size.x) * 0.5f, ImMax(0.0f, size.y - text_size.y) * 0.5f);
2916  RenderText(bb.Min + style.FramePadding + off, label);
2917  if (size.x < text_size.x || size.y < text_size.y)
2918  PopClipRect();
2919 
2920  return pressed;
2921 }

2951 // Upper-right button to close a window.
2952 static bool CloseWindowButton(bool* open)
2953 {
2954  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
2955 
2956  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID("##CLOSE");
2957  const float size = window->TitleBarHeight() - 4.0f;
2958  const ImGuiAabb bb(window->Aabb().GetTR() + ImVec2(-3.0f-size,2.0f), window->Aabb().GetTR() + ImVec2(-3.0f,2.0f+size));
2959 
2960  bool hovered, held;
2961  bool pressed = ButtonBehaviour(bb, id, &hovered, &held, true);
2962 
2963  // Render
2964  const ImU32 col = window->Color((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_CloseButtonActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_CloseButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_CloseButton);
2965  const ImVec2 center = bb.GetCenter();
2966  window->DrawList->AddCircleFilled(center, ImMax(2.0f,size*0.5f), col, 16);
2967 
2968  const float cross_extent = (size * 0.5f * 0.7071f) - 1.0f;
2969  if (hovered)
2970  {
2971  window->DrawList->AddLine(center + ImVec2(+cross_extent,+cross_extent), center + ImVec2(-cross_extent,-cross_extent), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Text));
2972  window->DrawList->AddLine(center + ImVec2(+cross_extent,-cross_extent), center + ImVec2(-cross_extent,+cross_extent), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Text));
2973  }
2974 
2975  if (open != NULL && pressed)
2976  *open = !*open;
2977 
2978  return pressed;
2979 }
