3047 
3048 bool CollapsingHeader(const char* label, const char* str_id, const bool display_frame, const bool default_open)
3049 {
3050  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3051  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3052  if (window->SkipItems)
3053  return false;
3054 
3055  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3056 
3057  IM_ASSERT(str_id != NULL || label != NULL);
3058  if (str_id == NULL)
3059  str_id = label;
3060  if (label == NULL)
3061  label = str_id;
3062  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(str_id);
3063 
3064  // We only write to the tree storage if the user clicks
3065  ImGuiStorage* tree = window->DC.StateStorage;
3066  bool opened;
3067  if (window->DC.OpenNextNode != -1)
3068  {
3069  opened = window->DC.OpenNextNode > 0;
3070  tree->SetInt(id, opened);
3071  window->DC.OpenNextNode = -1;
3072  }
3073  else
3074  {
3075  opened = tree->GetInt(id, default_open) != 0;
3076  }
3077 
3078  // Framed header expand a little outside the default padding
3079  const ImVec2 window_padding = window->WindowPadding();
3080  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
3081  const ImVec2 pos_min = window->DC.CursorPos;
3082  const ImVec2 pos_max = window->Pos + GetWindowContentRegionMax();
3083  ImGuiAabb bb = ImGuiAabb(pos_min, ImVec2(pos_max.x, pos_min.y + text_size.y));
3084  if (display_frame)
3085  {
3086  bb.Min.x -= window_padding.x*0.5f - 1;
3087  bb.Max.x += window_padding.x*0.5f - 1;
3088  bb.Max.y += style.FramePadding.y * 2;
3089  }
3090 
3091  const ImGuiAabb text_bb(bb.Min, bb.Min + ImVec2(window->FontSize() + style.FramePadding.x*2*2,0) + text_size);
3092  ItemSize(ImVec2(text_bb.GetSize().x, bb.GetSize().y)); // NB: we don't provide our width so that it doesn't get feed back into AutoFit
3093 
3094  // When logging is enabled, if automatically expand tree nodes (but *NOT* collapsing headers.. seems like sensible behaviour).
3095  // NB- If we are above max depth we still allow manually opened nodes to be logged.
3096  if (!display_frame)
3097  if (g.LogEnabled && window->DC.TreeDepth < g.LogAutoExpandMaxDepth)
3098  opened = true;
3099 
3100  if (ClipAdvance(bb))
3101  return opened;
3102 
3103  bool hovered, held;
3104  bool pressed = ButtonBehaviour(display_frame ? bb : text_bb, id, &hovered, &held, false);
3105  if (pressed)
3106  {
3107  opened = !opened;
3108  tree->SetInt(id, opened);
3109  }
3110 
3111  // Render
3112  const ImU32 col = window->Color((held && hovered) ? ImGuiCol_HeaderActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_HeaderHovered : ImGuiCol_Header);
3113  if (display_frame)
3114  {
3115  // Framed type
3116  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, true);
3117  RenderCollapseTriangle(bb.Min + style.FramePadding, opened, 1.0f, true);
3118  RenderText(bb.Min + style.FramePadding + ImVec2(window->FontSize() + style.FramePadding.x*2,0), label);
3119  }
3120  else
3121  {
3122  // Unframed typed for tree nodes
3123  if ((held && hovered) || hovered)
3124  RenderFrame(bb.Min, bb.Max, col, false);
3125  RenderCollapseTriangle(bb.Min + ImVec2(style.FramePadding.x, window->FontSize()*0.15f), opened, 0.70f, false);
3126  RenderText(bb.Min + ImVec2(window->FontSize() + style.FramePadding.x*2,0), label);
3127  }
3128 
3129  return opened;
3130 }

3252 void PopID()
3253 {
3254  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3255  window->IDStack.pop_back();
3256 }
3257 
3258 // User can input math operators (e.g. +100) to edit a numerical values.
3259 // NB: only call right after InputText because we are using its InitialValue storage
3260 static void ApplyNumericalTextInput(const char* buf, float *v)
3261 {
3262  while (*buf == ' ' || *buf == '\t')
3263  buf++;
3264 
3265  // We don't support '-' op because it would conflict with inputing negative value.
3266  // Instead you can use +-100 to subtract from an existing value
3267  char op = buf[0];
3268  if (op == '+' || op == '*' || op == '/')
3269  {
3270  buf++;
3271  while (*buf == ' ' || *buf == '\t')
3272  buf++;
3273  }
3274  else
3275  {
3276  op = 0;
3277  }
3278  if (!buf[0])
3279  return;
3280 
3281  float ref_v = *v;
3282  if (op)
3283  if (sscanf(GImGui.InputTextState.InitialText, "%f", &ref_v) < 1)
3284  return;
3285 
3286  float op_v = 0.0f;
3287  if (sscanf(buf, "%f", &op_v) < 1)
3288  return;
3289 
3290  if (op == '+')
3291  *v = ref_v + op_v;
3292  else if (op == '*')
3293  *v = ref_v * op_v;
3294  else if (op == '/')
3295  {
3296  if (op_v == 0.0f)
3297  return;
3298  *v = ref_v / op_v;
3299  }
3300  else
3301  *v = op_v;
3302 }
3303 
3304 // Use power!=1.0 for logarithmic sliders.
3305 // Adjust display_format to decorate the value with a prefix or a suffix.
3306 bool SliderFloat(const char* label, float* v, float v_min, float v_max, const char* display_format, float power)
3307 {
3308  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3309  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3310  if (window->SkipItems)
3311  return false;
3312 
3313  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3314  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
3315  const float w = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
3316 
3317  if (!display_format)
3318  display_format = "%.3f";
3319 
3320  // Dodgily parse display precision back from the display format
3321  int decimal_precision = 3;
3322  if (const char* p = strchr(display_format, '%'))
3323  {
3324  p++;
3325  while (*p >= '0' && *p <= '9')
3326  p++;
3327  if (*p == '.')
3328  {
3329  decimal_precision = atoi(p+1);
3330  if (decimal_precision < 0 || decimal_precision > 10)
3331  decimal_precision = 3;
3332  }
3333  }
3334 
3335  const bool tab_focus_requested = window->FocusItemRegister(g.ActiveId == id);
3336 
3337  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
3338  const ImGuiAabb frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, text_size.y) + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
3339  const ImGuiAabb slider_bb(frame_bb.Min+g.Style.FramePadding, frame_bb.Max-g.Style.FramePadding);
3340  const ImGuiAabb bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + text_size.x, 0.0f));
3341 
3342  if (IsClipped(slider_bb))
3343  {
3344  // NB- we don't use ClipAdvance() in the if() statement because we don't want to submit ItemSize() because we may change into a text edit later which may submit an ItemSize itself
3345  ItemSize(bb);
3346  return false;
3347  }
3348 
3349  const bool is_unbound = v_min == -FLT_MAX || v_min == FLT_MAX || v_max == -FLT_MAX || v_max == FLT_MAX;
3350 
3351  const float grab_size_in_units = 1.0f; // In 'v' units. Probably needs to be parametrized, based on a 'v_step' value? decimal precision?
3352  float grab_size_in_pixels;
3353  if (decimal_precision > 0 || is_unbound)
3354  grab_size_in_pixels = 10.0f;
3355  else
3356  grab_size_in_pixels = ImMax(grab_size_in_units * (w / (v_max-v_min+1.0f)), 8.0f); // Integer sliders
3357  const float slider_effective_w = slider_bb.GetWidth() - grab_size_in_pixels;
3358  const float slider_effective_x1 = slider_bb.Min.x + grab_size_in_pixels*0.5f;
3359  const float slider_effective_x2 = slider_bb.Max.x - grab_size_in_pixels*0.5f;
3360 
3361  // For logarithmic sliders that cross over sign boundary we want the exponential increase to be symetric around 0.0f
3362  float linear_zero_pos = 0.0f; // 0.0->1.0f
3363  if (!is_unbound)
3364  {
3365  if (v_min * v_max < 0.0f)
3366  {
3367  // Different sign
3368  const float linear_dist_min_to_0 = powf(fabsf(0.0f - v_min), 1.0f/power);
3369  const float linear_dist_max_to_0 = powf(fabsf(v_max - 0.0f), 1.0f/power);
3370  linear_zero_pos = linear_dist_min_to_0 / (linear_dist_min_to_0+linear_dist_max_to_0);
3371  }
3372  else
3373  {
3374  // Same sign
3375  linear_zero_pos = v_min < 0.0f ? 1.0f : 0.0f;
3376  }
3377  }
3378 
3379  const bool hovered = (g.HoveredWindow == window) && (g.HoveredId == 0) && IsMouseHoveringBox(slider_bb);
3380  if (hovered)
3381  g.HoveredId = id;
3382 
3383  bool start_text_input = false;
3384  if (tab_focus_requested || (hovered && g.IO.MouseClicked[0]))
3385  {
3386  g.ActiveId = id;
3387 
3388  const bool is_ctrl_down = g.IO.KeyCtrl;
3389  if (tab_focus_requested || is_ctrl_down || is_unbound)
3390  {
3391  start_text_input = true;
3392  g.SliderAsInputTextId = 0;
3393  }
3394  }
3395 
3396  // Tabbing or CTRL-clicking through slider turns into an input box
3397  bool value_changed = false;
3398  if (start_text_input || (g.ActiveId == id && id == g.SliderAsInputTextId))
3399  {
3400  char text_buf[64];
3401  ImFormatString(text_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(text_buf), "%.*f", decimal_precision, *v);
3402 
3403  g.ActiveId = g.SliderAsInputTextId;
3404  g.HoveredId = 0;
3405  window->FocusItemUnregister(); // Our replacement slider will override the focus ID (that we needed to declare previously to allow for a TAB focus to happen before we got selected)
3406  value_changed = ImGui::InputText(label, text_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(text_buf), ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal | ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll);
3407  if (g.SliderAsInputTextId == 0)
3408  {
3409  // First frame
3410  IM_ASSERT(g.ActiveId == id); // InputText ID should match the Slider ID (else we'd need to store them both which is also possible)
3411  g.SliderAsInputTextId = g.ActiveId;
3412  g.ActiveId = id;
3413  g.HoveredId = id;
3414  }
3415  else
3416  {
3417  if (g.ActiveId == g.SliderAsInputTextId)
3418  g.ActiveId = id;
3419  else
3420  g.ActiveId = g.SliderAsInputTextId = 0;
3421  }
3422  if (value_changed)
3423  {
3424  ApplyNumericalTextInput(text_buf, v);
3425  }
3426  return value_changed;
3427  }
3428 
3429  ItemSize(bb);
3430  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, window->Color(ImGuiCol_FrameBg));
3431 
3432  if (g.ActiveId == id)
3433  {
3434  if (g.IO.MouseDown[0])
3435  {
3436  if (!is_unbound)
3437  {
3438  const float normalized_pos = ImClamp((g.IO.MousePos.x - slider_effective_x1) / slider_effective_w, 0.0f, 1.0f);
3439 
3440  // Linear slider
3441  //float new_value = ImLerp(v_min, v_max, normalized_pos);
3442 
3443  // Account for logarithmic scale on both sides of the zero
3444  float new_value;
3445  if (normalized_pos < linear_zero_pos)
3446  {
3447  // Negative: rescale to the negative range before powering
3448  float a = 1.0f - (normalized_pos / linear_zero_pos);
3449  a = powf(a, power);
3450  new_value = ImLerp(ImMin(v_max,0.f), v_min, a);
3451  }
3452  else
3453  {
3454  // Positive: rescale to the positive range before powering
3455  float a;
3456  if (fabsf(linear_zero_pos - 1.0f) > 1.e-6)
3457  a = (normalized_pos - linear_zero_pos) / (1.0f - linear_zero_pos);
3458  else
3459  a = normalized_pos;
3460  a = powf(a, power);
3461  new_value = ImLerp(ImMax(v_min,0.0f), v_max, a);
3462  }
3463 
3464  // Round past decimal precision
3465  // 0: 1
3466  // 1: 0.1
3467  // 2: 0.01
3468  // etc..
3469  // So when our value is 1.99999 with a precision of 0.001 we'll end up rounding to 2.0
3470  const float min_step = 1.0f / powf(10.0f, (float)decimal_precision);
3471  const float remainder = fmodf(new_value, min_step);
3472  if (remainder <= min_step*0.5f)
3473  new_value -= remainder;
3474  else
3475  new_value += (min_step - remainder);
3476 
3477  if (*v != new_value)
3478  {
3479  *v = new_value;
3480  value_changed = true;
3481  }
3482  }
3483  }
3484  else
3485  {
3486  g.ActiveId = 0;
3487  }
3488  }
3489 
3490  if (!is_unbound)
3491  {
3492  // Linear slider
3493  // const float grab_t = (ImClamp(*v, v_min, v_max) - v_min) / (v_max - v_min);
3494 
3495  // Calculate slider grab positioning
3496  float grab_t;
3497  float v_clamped = ImClamp(*v, v_min, v_max);
3498  if (v_clamped < 0.0f)
3499  {
3500  const float f = 1.0f - (v_clamped - v_min) / (ImMin(0.0f,v_max) - v_min);
3501  grab_t = (1.0f - powf(f, 1.0f/power)) * linear_zero_pos;
3502  }
3503  else
3504  {
3505  const float f = (v_clamped - ImMax(0.0f,v_min)) / (v_max - ImMax(0.0f,v_min));
3506  grab_t = linear_zero_pos + powf(f, 1.0f/power) * (1.0f - linear_zero_pos);
3507  }
3508 
3509  // Draw
3510  const float grab_x = ImLerp(slider_effective_x1, slider_effective_x2, grab_t);
3511  const ImGuiAabb grab_bb(ImVec2(grab_x-grab_size_in_pixels*0.5f,frame_bb.Min.y+2.0f), ImVec2(grab_x+grab_size_in_pixels*0.5f,frame_bb.Max.y-2.0f));
3512  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(grab_bb.Min, grab_bb.Max, window->Color(g.ActiveId == id ? ImGuiCol_SliderGrabActive : ImGuiCol_SliderGrab));
3513  }
3514 
3515  // Draw value using user-provided display format so user can add prefix/suffix/decorations to the value.
3516  char value_buf[64];
3517  ImFormatString(value_buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(value_buf), display_format, *v);
3518  RenderText(ImVec2(slider_bb.GetCenter().x-CalcTextSize(value_buf).x*0.5f, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), value_buf);
3519 
3520  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, slider_bb.Min.y), label);
3521 
3522  return value_changed;
3523 }

3525 bool SliderAngle(const char* label, float* v, float v_degrees_min, float v_degrees_max)
3526 {
3527  float v_deg = *v * 360.0f / (2*PI);
3528  bool changed = ImGui::SliderFloat(label, &v_deg, v_degrees_min, v_degrees_max, "%.0f deg", 1.0f);
3529  *v = v_deg * (2*PI) / 360.0f;
3530  return changed;
3531 }

3543 static bool SliderFloatN(const char* label, float v[3], int components, float v_min, float v_max, const char* display_format, float power)
3544 {
3545  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3546  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3547  if (window->SkipItems)
3548  return false;
3549 
3550  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3551  const float w_full = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
3552  const float w_item_one = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)((w_full - (style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x)*(components-1)) / (float)components));
3553  const float w_item_last = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(w_full - (w_item_one+style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x)*(components-1)));
3554 
3555  bool value_changed = false;
3556  ImGui::PushID(label);
3557  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_one);
3558  for (int i = 0; i < components; i++)
3559  {
3560  ImGui::PushID(i);
3561  if (i + 1 == components)
3562  {
3563  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
3564  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_last);
3565  }
3566  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderFloat("##v", &v[i], v_min, v_max, display_format, power);
3567  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
3568  ImGui::PopID();
3569  }
3570  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
3571  ImGui::PopID();
3572 
3573  ImGui::TextUnformatted(label, FindTextDisplayEnd(label));
3574 
3575  return value_changed;
3576 }

3600 static float PlotGetValue(const float* values, size_t stride, int idx)
3601 {
3602  const float v = *(float*)((unsigned char*)values + (size_t)idx * stride);
3603  return v;

3606 static void Plot(ImGuiPlotType plot_type, const char* label, const float* values, int values_count, int values_offset, const char* overlay_text, float scale_min, float scale_max, ImVec2 graph_size, size_t stride)
3607 {
3608  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3609  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3610  if (window->SkipItems)
3611  return;
3612 
3613  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3614 
3615  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
3616  if (graph_size.x == 0)
3617  graph_size.x = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
3618  if (graph_size.y == 0)
3619  graph_size.y = text_size.y;
3620 
3621  const ImGuiAabb frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(graph_size.x, graph_size.y) + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
3622  const ImGuiAabb graph_bb(frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, frame_bb.Max - style.FramePadding);
3623  const ImGuiAabb bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + text_size.x,0));
3624  ItemSize(bb);
3625 
3626  if (ClipAdvance(bb))
3627  return;
3628 
3629  // Determine scale if not specified
3630  if (scale_min == FLT_MAX || scale_max == FLT_MAX)
3631  {
3632  float v_min = FLT_MAX;
3633  float v_max = -FLT_MAX;
3634  for (int i = 0; i < values_count; i++)
3635  {
3636  const float v = PlotGetValue(values, stride, i);
3637  v_min = ImMin(v_min, v);
3638  v_max = ImMax(v_max, v);
3639  }
3640  if (scale_min == FLT_MAX)
3641  scale_min = v_min;
3642  if (scale_max == FLT_MAX)
3643  scale_max = v_max;
3644  }
3645 
3646  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, window->Color(ImGuiCol_FrameBg));
3647 
3648  int res_w = ImMin((int)graph_size.x, values_count);
3649  if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines)
3650  res_w -= 1;
3651 
3652  // Tooltip on hover
3653  int v_hovered = -1;
3654  if (IsMouseHoveringBox(graph_bb))
3655  {
3656  const float t = ImClamp((g.IO.MousePos.x - graph_bb.Min.x) / (graph_bb.Max.x - graph_bb.Min.x), 0.0f, 0.9999f);
3657  const int v_idx = (int)(t * (values_count + ((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? -1 : 0)));
3658  IM_ASSERT(v_idx >= 0 && v_idx < values_count);
3659 
3660  const float v0 = PlotGetValue(values, stride, (v_idx + values_offset) % values_count);
3661  const float v1 = PlotGetValue(values, stride, (v_idx + 1 + values_offset) % values_count);
3662  if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines)
3663  ImGui::SetTooltip("%d: %8.4g\n%d: %8.4g", v_idx, v0, v_idx+1, v1);
3664  else if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Histogram)
3665  ImGui::SetTooltip("%d: %8.4g", v_idx, v0);
3666  v_hovered = v_idx;
3667  }
3668 
3669  const float t_step = 1.0f / (float)res_w;
3670 
3671  float v0 = PlotGetValue(values, stride, (0 + values_offset) % values_count);
3672  float t0 = 0.0f;
3673  ImVec2 p0 = ImVec2( t0, 1.0f - ImSaturate((v0 - scale_min) / (scale_max - scale_min)) );
3674 
3675  const ImU32 col_base = window->Color((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? ImGuiCol_PlotLines : ImGuiCol_PlotHistogram);
3676  const ImU32 col_hovered = window->Color((plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines) ? ImGuiCol_PlotLinesHovered : ImGuiCol_PlotHistogramHovered);
3677 
3678  for (int n = 0; n < res_w; n++)
3679  {
3680  const float t1 = t0 + t_step;
3681  const int v_idx = (int)(t0 * values_count);
3682  IM_ASSERT(v_idx >= 0 && v_idx < values_count);
3683  const float v1 = PlotGetValue(values, stride, (v_idx + values_offset + 1) % values_count);
3684  const ImVec2 p1 = ImVec2( t1, 1.0f - ImSaturate((v1 - scale_min) / (scale_max - scale_min)) );
3685 
3686  // NB- Draw calls are merged together by the DrawList system.
3687  if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Lines)
3688  window->DrawList->AddLine(ImLerp(graph_bb.Min, graph_bb.Max, p0), ImLerp(graph_bb.Min, graph_bb.Max, p1), v_hovered == v_idx ? col_hovered : col_base);
3689  else if (plot_type == ImGuiPlotType_Histogram)
3690  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(ImLerp(graph_bb.Min, graph_bb.Max, p0), ImLerp(graph_bb.Min, graph_bb.Max, ImVec2(p1.x, 1.0f))+ImVec2(-1,0), v_hovered == v_idx ? col_hovered : col_base);
3691 
3692  t0 = t1;
3693  p0 = p1;
3694  }
3695 
3696  // Text overlay
3697  if (overlay_text)
3698  RenderText(ImVec2(graph_bb.GetCenter().x-CalcTextSize(overlay_text).x*0.5f, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), overlay_text);
3699 
3700  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, graph_bb.Min.y), label);
3701 }

3713 bool Checkbox(const char* label, bool* v)
3714 {
3715  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3716  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3717  if (window->SkipItems)
3718  return false;
3719 
3720  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3721  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
3722 
3723  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
3724 
3725  const ImGuiAabb check_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(text_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2, text_size.y + style.FramePadding.y*2));
3726  ItemSize(check_bb);
3727  SameLine(0, (int)g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
3728 
3729  const ImGuiAabb text_bb(window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(0,style.FramePadding.y), window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(0,style.FramePadding.y) + text_size);
3730  ItemSize(ImVec2(text_bb.GetWidth(), check_bb.GetHeight()));
3731  const ImGuiAabb total_bb(ImMin(check_bb.Min, text_bb.Min), ImMax(check_bb.Max, text_bb.Max));
3732 
3733  if (ClipAdvance(total_bb))
3734  return false;
3735 
3736  const bool hovered = (g.HoveredWindow == window) && (g.HoveredId == 0) && IsMouseHoveringBox(total_bb);
3737  const bool pressed = hovered && g.IO.MouseClicked[0];
3738  if (hovered)
3739  g.HoveredId = id;
3740  if (pressed)
3741  {
3742  *v = !(*v);
3743  g.ActiveId = 0; // Clear focus
3744  }
3745 
3746  RenderFrame(check_bb.Min, check_bb.Max, window->Color(hovered ? ImGuiCol_CheckHovered : ImGuiCol_FrameBg));
3747  if (*v)
3748  {
3749  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(check_bb.Min+ImVec2(3,3), check_bb.Max-ImVec2(3,3), window->Color(ImGuiCol_CheckActive));
3750  }
3751 
3752  if (g.LogEnabled)
3753  LogText(text_bb.GetTL(), *v ? "[x]" : "[ ]");
3754  RenderText(text_bb.GetTL(), label);
3755 
3756  return pressed;
3757 }

3811  }

3814  LogText(text_bb.GetTL(), active ? "(x)" : "( )");
3815  RenderText(text_bb.GetTL(), label);
3816

3832 // Wrapper for stb_textedit.h to edit text (our wrapper is for: statically sized buffer, single-line, ASCII, fixed-width font)
3833 int STB_TEXTEDIT_STRINGLEN(const STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj) { return (int)ImStrlenW(obj->Text); }
3834 ImWchar STB_TEXTEDIT_GETCHAR(const STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx) { return obj->Text[idx]; }
3835 float STB_TEXTEDIT_GETWIDTH(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int line_start_idx, int char_idx) { (void)line_start_idx; return obj->Font->CalcTextSizeW(obj->FontSize, 0, &obj->Text[char_idx], &obj->Text[char_idx]+1, NULL).x; }
3836 int STB_TEXTEDIT_KEYTOTEXT(int key) { return key >= 0x10000 ? 0 : key; }
3837 ImWchar STB_TEXTEDIT_NEWLINE = '\n';
3838 void STB_TEXTEDIT_LAYOUTROW(StbTexteditRow* r, STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int line_start_idx)
3839 {
3840  const ImWchar* text_remaining = NULL;
3841  const ImVec2 size = obj->Font->CalcTextSizeW(obj->FontSize, FLT_MAX, obj->Text + line_start_idx, NULL, &text_remaining);
3842  r->x0 = 0.0f;
3843  r->x1 = size.x;
3844  r->baseline_y_delta = size.y;
3845  r->ymin = 0.0f;
3846  r->ymax = size.y;
3847  r->num_chars = (int)(text_remaining - (obj->Text + line_start_idx));
3848 }

3850 static bool is_white(unsigned int c) { return c==0 || c==' ' || c=='\t' || c=='\r' || c=='\n'; }
3851 static bool is_separator(unsigned int c) { return c==',' || c==';' || c=='(' || c==')' || c=='{' || c=='}' || c=='[' || c==']' || c=='|'; }
3852 
3853 #define STB_TEXTEDIT_IS_SPACE(c) (is_white((unsigned int)c) || is_separator((unsigned int)c))
3854 void STB_TEXTEDIT_DELETECHARS(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx, int n) { ImWchar* dst = obj->Text+idx; const ImWchar* src = obj->Text+idx+n; while (ImWchar c = *src++) *dst++ = c; *dst = '\0'; }
3855 
3856 bool STB_TEXTEDIT_INSERTCHARS(STB_TEXTEDIT_STRING* obj, int idx, const ImWchar* new_text, int new_text_len)
3857 {
3858  ImWchar* buf_end = obj->Text + obj->BufSize;
3859  const size_t text_len = ImStrlenW(obj->Text);
3860 
3861  if (new_text_len > buf_end - (obj->Text + text_len + 1))
3862  return false;
3863 
3864  memmove(obj->Text + (size_t)idx + new_text_len, obj->Text + (size_t)idx, (text_len - (size_t)idx) * sizeof(ImWchar));
3865  memcpy(obj->Text + (size_t)idx, new_text, (size_t)new_text_len * sizeof(ImWchar));
3866  obj->Text[text_len + (size_t)new_text_len] = 0;
3867 
3868  return true;
3869 }

3876  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DOWN, // keyboard input to move cursor down
3877  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART, // keyboard input to move cursor to start of line
3878  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINEEND, // keyboard input to move cursor to end of line
3879  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTSTART, // keyboard input to move cursor to start of text
3880  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTEND, // keyboard input to move cursor to end of text
3881  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DELETE, // keyboard input to delete selection or character under cursor
3882  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_BACKSPACE, // keyboard input to delete selection or character left of cursor
3883  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UNDO, // keyboard input to perform undo
3884  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_REDO, // keyboard input to perform redo
3885  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT, // keyboard input to move cursor left one word
3886  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDRIGHT, // keyboard input to move cursor right one word
3887  STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT = 1 << 17,

3899 void ImGuiTextEditState::UpdateScrollOffset()
3900 {
3901  // Scroll in chunks of quarter width
3902  const float scroll_x_increment = Width * 0.25f;
3903  const float cursor_offset_x = Font->CalcTextSizeW(FontSize, 0, Text, Text+StbState.cursor, NULL).x;
3904  if (ScrollX > cursor_offset_x)
3905  ScrollX = ImMax(0.0f, cursor_offset_x - scroll_x_increment);
3906  else if (ScrollX < cursor_offset_x - Width)
3907  ScrollX = cursor_offset_x - Width + scroll_x_increment;
3908 }

3910 ImVec2 ImGuiTextEditState::CalcDisplayOffsetFromCharIdx(int i) const
3911 {
3912  const ImWchar* text_start = GetTextPointerClippedW(Font, FontSize, Text, ScrollX, NULL);
3913  const ImWchar* text_end = (Text+i >= text_start) ? Text+i : text_start; // Clip if requested character is outside of display
3914  IM_ASSERT(text_end >= text_start);
3915 
3916  const ImVec2 offset = Font->CalcTextSizeW(FontSize, Width, text_start, text_end, NULL);
3917  return offset;
3918 }

3930  return text_clipped_end;
3931 }

3946 // [Static]
3947 void ImGuiTextEditState::RenderTextScrolledClipped(ImFont font, float font_size, const char* buf, ImVec2 pos, float width, float scroll_x)
3948 {
3949  // NB- We start drawing at character boundary
3950  ImVec2 text_size;
3951  const char* text_start = GetTextPointerClippedA(font, font_size, buf, scroll_x, NULL);
3952  const char* text_end = GetTextPointerClippedA(font, font_size, text_start, width, &text_size);
3953 
3954  // Draw a little clip symbol if we've got text on either left or right of the box
3955  const char symbol_c = '~';
3956  const float symbol_w = font_size*0.40f; // FIXME: compute correct width
3957  const float clip_begin = (text_start > buf && text_start < text_end) ? symbol_w : 0.0f;
3958  const float clip_end = (text_end[0] != '\0' && text_end > text_start) ? symbol_w : 0.0f;
3959 
3960  // Draw text
3961  ImGui::RenderText(pos+ImVec2(clip_begin,0), text_start+(clip_begin>0.0f?1:0), text_end-(clip_end>0.0f?1:0), false);//, &text_params_with_clipping);
3962 
3963  // Draw the clip symbol
3964  const char s[2] = {symbol_c,'\0'};
3965  if (clip_begin > 0.0f)
3966  ImGui::RenderText(pos, s);
3967  if (clip_end > 0.0f)
3968  ImGui::RenderText(pos+ImVec2(width-clip_end,0.0f), s);
3969 }

3974 bool InputFloat(const char* label, float *v, float step, float step_fast, int decimal_precision, ImGuiInputTextFlags extra_flags)
3975 {
3976  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
3977  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
3978  if (window->SkipItems)
3979  return false;
3980 
3981  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
3982  const float w = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
3983  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
3984  const ImGuiAabb frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, text_size.y) + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
3985 
3986  ImGui::PushID(label);
3987  const float button_sz = window->FontSize();
3988  if (step > 0.0f)
3989  ImGui::PushItemWidth(ImMax(1.0f, window->DC.ItemWidth.back() - (button_sz+g.Style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x)*2));
3990 
3991  char buf[64];
3992  if (decimal_precision < 0)
3993  ImFormatString(buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), "%f", *v); // Ideally we'd have a minimum decimal precision of 1 to visually denote that it is a float, while hiding non-significant digits?
3994  else
3995  ImFormatString(buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), "%.*f", decimal_precision, *v);
3996  bool value_changed = false;
3997  const ImGuiInputTextFlags flags = extra_flags | (ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal|ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll);
3998  if (ImGui::InputText("", buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), flags))
3999  {
4000  ApplyNumericalTextInput(buf, v);
4001  value_changed = true;
4002  }
4003 
4004  // Step buttons
4005  if (step > 0.0f)
4006  {
4007  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4008  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4009  if (ImGui::Button("-", ImVec2(button_sz,button_sz), true))
4010  {
4011  *v -= g.IO.KeyCtrl && step_fast > 0.0f ? step_fast : step;
4012  value_changed = true;
4013  }
4014  ImGui::SameLine(0, (int)g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4015  if (ImGui::Button("+", ImVec2(button_sz,button_sz), true))
4016  {
4017  *v += g.IO.KeyCtrl && step_fast > 0.0f ? step_fast : step;
4018  value_changed = true;
4019  }
4020  }
4021 
4022  ImGui::PopID();
4023 
4024  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + g.Style.FramePadding.y), label);
4025 
4026  //ImGui::SameLine(0, (int)g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4027  //ImGui::TextUnformatted(label, FindTextDisplayEnd(label));
4028 
4029  return value_changed;
4030 }

4040 bool InputText(const char* label, char* buf, size_t buf_size, ImGuiInputTextFlags flags)
4041 {
4042  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4043  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4044  if (window->SkipItems)
4045  return false;
4046 
4047  const ImGuiIO& io = g.IO;
4048  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
4049 
4050  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
4051  const float w = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
4052 
4053  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
4054  const ImGuiAabb frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(w, text_size.y) + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
4055  const ImGuiAabb bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + text_size.x, 0.0f));
4056  ItemSize(bb);
4057 
4058  if (ClipAdvance(frame_bb))
4059  return false;
4060 
4061  // NB: we can only read/write to 'edit_state' if we are the active widget!
4062  ImGuiTextEditState& edit_state = g.InputTextState;
4063 
4064  const bool is_ctrl_down = io.KeyCtrl;
4065  const bool is_shift_down = io.KeyShift;
4066  const bool tab_focus_requested = window->FocusItemRegister(g.ActiveId == id);
4067  //const bool align_center = (bool)(flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AlignCenter); // FIXME: Unsupported
4068 
4069  const bool hovered = (g.HoveredWindow == window) && (g.HoveredId == 0) && IsMouseHoveringBox(frame_bb);
4070  if (hovered)
4071  g.HoveredId = id;
4072 
4073  bool select_all = (g.ActiveId != id) && (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_AutoSelectAll) != 0;
4074  if (tab_focus_requested || (hovered && io.MouseClicked[0]))
4075  {
4076  if (g.ActiveId != id)
4077  {
4078  // Start edition
4079  // Take a copy of the initial buffer value (both in original UTF-8 format and converted to wchar)
4080  ImFormatString(edit_state.InitialText, IM_ARRAYSIZE(edit_state.InitialText), "%s", buf);
4081  ImTextStrFromUtf8(edit_state.Text, IM_ARRAYSIZE(edit_state.Text), buf, NULL);
4082  edit_state.ScrollX = 0.0f;
4083  edit_state.Width = w;
4084  stb_textedit_initialize_state(&edit_state.StbState, true);
4085  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
4086  edit_state.LastCursorPos = ImVec2(-1.f,-1.f);
4087 
4088  if (tab_focus_requested || is_ctrl_down)
4089  select_all = true;
4090  }
4091  g.ActiveId = id;
4092  }
4093  else if (io.MouseClicked[0])
4094  {
4095  // Release focus when we click outside
4096  if (g.ActiveId == id)
4097  {
4098  g.ActiveId = 0;
4099  }
4100  }
4101 
4102  bool value_changed = false;
4103  bool cancel_edit = false;
4104  bool enter_pressed = false;
4105  static char text_tmp_utf8[IM_ARRAYSIZE(edit_state.InitialText)];
4106  if (g.ActiveId == id)
4107  {
4108  // Edit in progress
4109  edit_state.BufSize = buf_size < IM_ARRAYSIZE(edit_state.Text) ? buf_size : IM_ARRAYSIZE(edit_state.Text);
4110  edit_state.Font = window->Font();
4111  edit_state.FontSize = window->FontSize();
4112 
4113  const float mx = g.IO.MousePos.x - frame_bb.Min.x - style.FramePadding.x;
4114  const float my = window->FontSize()*0.5f; // Better for single line
4115 
4116  edit_state.UpdateScrollOffset();
4117  if (select_all || (hovered && io.MouseDoubleClicked[0]))
4118  {
4119  edit_state.SelectAll();
4120  edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock = true;
4121  }
4122  else if (io.MouseClicked[0] && !edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock)
4123  {
4124  stb_textedit_click(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, mx + edit_state.ScrollX, my);
4125  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
4126 
4127  }
4128  else if (io.MouseDown[0] && !edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock)
4129  {
4130  stb_textedit_drag(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, mx + edit_state.ScrollX, my);
4131  edit_state.CursorAnimReset();
4132  }
4133  if (edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock && !io.MouseDown[0])
4134  edit_state.SelectedAllMouseLock = false;
4135 
4136  const int k_mask = (is_shift_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_SHIFT : 0);
4137  if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_LeftArrow)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(is_ctrl_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDLEFT | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LEFT | k_mask);
4138  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_RightArrow)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(is_ctrl_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_WORDRIGHT | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_RIGHT | k_mask);
4139  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_UpArrow)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UP | k_mask);
4140  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_DownArrow)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DOWN | k_mask);
4141  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Home)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(is_ctrl_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTSTART | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINESTART | k_mask);
4142  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_End)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(is_ctrl_down ? STB_TEXTEDIT_K_TEXTEND | k_mask : STB_TEXTEDIT_K_LINEEND | k_mask);
4143  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Delete)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_DELETE | k_mask);
4144  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Backspace)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_BACKSPACE | k_mask);
4145  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Enter)) { g.ActiveId = 0; enter_pressed = true; }
4146  else if (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Escape)) { g.ActiveId = 0; cancel_edit = true; }
4147  else if (is_ctrl_down && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Z)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_UNDO); // I don't want to use shortcuts but we should probably have an Input-catch stack
4148  else if (is_ctrl_down && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_Y)) edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(STB_TEXTEDIT_K_REDO);
4149  else if (is_ctrl_down && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_A)) edit_state.SelectAll();
4150  else if (is_ctrl_down && (IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_X) || IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_C)))
4151  {
4152  // Cut, Copy
4153  const bool cut = IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_X);
4154  if (cut && !edit_state.HasSelection())
4155  edit_state.SelectAll();
4156 
4157  if (g.IO.SetClipboardTextFn)
4158  {
4159  const int ib = edit_state.HasSelection() ? ImMin(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end) : 0;
4160  const int ie = edit_state.HasSelection() ? ImMax(edit_state.StbState.select_start, edit_state.StbState.select_end) : (int)ImStrlenW(edit_state.Text);
4161  ImTextStrToUtf8(text_tmp_utf8, IM_ARRAYSIZE(text_tmp_utf8), edit_state.Text+ib, edit_state.Text+ie);
4162  g.IO.SetClipboardTextFn(text_tmp_utf8);
4163  }
4164 
4165  if (cut)
4166  stb_textedit_cut(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState);
4167  }
4168  else if (is_ctrl_down && IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiKey_V))
4169  {
4170  // Paste
4171  if (g.IO.GetClipboardTextFn)
4172  {
4173  if (const char* clipboard = g.IO.GetClipboardTextFn())
4174  {
4175  // Remove new-line from pasted buffer
4176  size_t clipboard_len = strlen(clipboard);
4177  ImWchar* clipboard_filtered = (ImWchar*)ImGui::MemAlloc((clipboard_len+1) * sizeof(ImWchar));
4178  int clipboard_filtered_len = 0;
4179  for (const char* s = clipboard; *s; )
4180  {
4181  unsigned int c;
4182  const int bytes_count = ImTextCharFromUtf8(&c, s, NULL);
4183  if (bytes_count <= 0)
4184  break;
4185  s += bytes_count;
4186  if (c == '\n' || c == '\r')
4187  continue;
4188  clipboard_filtered[clipboard_filtered_len++] = c;
4189  }
4190  clipboard_filtered[clipboard_filtered_len] = 0;
4191  stb_textedit_paste(&edit_state, &edit_state.StbState, clipboard_filtered, clipboard_filtered_len);
4192  ImGui::MemFree(clipboard_filtered);
4193  }
4194  }
4195  }
4196  else if (g.IO.InputCharacters[0])
4197  {
4198  // Text input
4199  for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(g.IO.InputCharacters) && g.IO.InputCharacters[n]; n++)
4200  {
4201  const ImWchar c = g.IO.InputCharacters[n];
4202  if (c)
4203  {
4204  // Filter
4205  if (c < 256 && !isprint((char)(c & 0xFF)) && c != ' ')
4206  continue;
4207  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsDecimal)
4208  if (!(c >= '0' && c <= '9') && (c != '.') && (c != '-') && (c != '+') && (c != '*') && (c != '/'))
4209  continue;
4210  if (flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal)
4211  if (!(c >= '0' && c <= '9') && !(c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') && !(c >= 'A' && c <= 'F'))
4212  continue;
4213 
4214  // Insert character!
4215  edit_state.OnKeyboardPressed(c);
4216  }
4217  }
4218  }
4219 
4220  edit_state.CursorAnim += g.IO.DeltaTime;
4221  edit_state.UpdateScrollOffset();
4222 
4223  if (cancel_edit)
4224  {
4225  // Restore initial value
4226  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%s", edit_state.InitialText);
4227  value_changed = true;
4228  }
4229  else
4230  {
4231  // Apply new value immediately - copy modified buffer back
4232  // Note that as soon as we can focus into the input box, the in-widget value gets priority over any underlying modification of the input buffer
4233  // FIXME: We actually always render 'buf' in RenderTextScrolledClipped
4234  // FIXME-OPT: CPU waste to do this everytime the widget is active, should mark dirty state from the textedit callbacks
4235  ImTextStrToUtf8(text_tmp_utf8, IM_ARRAYSIZE(text_tmp_utf8), edit_state.Text, NULL);
4236  if (strcmp(text_tmp_utf8, buf) != 0)
4237  {
4238  ImFormatString(buf, buf_size, "%s", text_tmp_utf8);
4239  value_changed = true;
4240  }
4241  }
4242  }
4243 
4244  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, window->Color(ImGuiCol_FrameBg), true);//, style.Rounding);
4245 
4246  const ImVec2 font_off_up = ImVec2(0.0f,window->FontSize()+1.0f); // FIXME: this should be part of the font API
4247  const ImVec2 font_off_dn = ImVec2(0.0f,2.0f);
4248 
4249  if (g.ActiveId == id)
4250  {
4251  // Draw selection
4252  const int select_begin_idx = edit_state.StbState.select_start;
4253  const int select_end_idx = edit_state.StbState.select_end;
4254  if (select_begin_idx != select_end_idx)
4255  {
4256  const ImVec2 select_begin_pos = frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding + edit_state.CalcDisplayOffsetFromCharIdx(ImMin(select_begin_idx,select_end_idx));
4257  const ImVec2 select_end_pos = frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding + edit_state.CalcDisplayOffsetFromCharIdx(ImMax(select_begin_idx,select_end_idx));
4258  window->DrawList->AddRectFilled(select_begin_pos - font_off_up, select_end_pos + font_off_dn, window->Color(ImGuiCol_TextSelectedBg));
4259  }
4260  }
4261 
4262  // FIXME: 'align_center' unsupported
4263  ImGuiTextEditState::RenderTextScrolledClipped(window->Font(), window->FontSize(), buf, frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, w, (g.ActiveId == id) ? edit_state.ScrollX : 0.0f);
4264 
4265  if (g.ActiveId == id)
4266  {
4267  const ImVec2 cursor_pos = frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding + edit_state.CalcDisplayOffsetFromCharIdx(edit_state.StbState.cursor);
4268 
4269  // Draw blinking cursor
4270  if (g.InputTextState.CursorIsVisible())
4271  window->DrawList->AddRect(cursor_pos - font_off_up + ImVec2(0,2), cursor_pos + font_off_dn - ImVec2(0,3), window->Color(ImGuiCol_Text));
4272 
4273  // Notify OS of text input position
4274  if (io.ImeSetInputScreenPosFn && ImLength(edit_state.LastCursorPos - cursor_pos) > 0.01f)
4275  io.ImeSetInputScreenPosFn((int)cursor_pos.x - 1, (int)(cursor_pos.y - window->FontSize())); // -1 x offset so that Windows IME can cover our cursor. Bit of an extra nicety.
4276 
4277  edit_state.LastCursorPos = cursor_pos;
4278  }
4279 
4280  RenderText(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x, frame_bb.Min.y + style.FramePadding.y), label);
4281 
4282  if ((flags & ImGuiInputTextFlags_EnterReturnsTrue) != 0)
4283  return enter_pressed;
4284  else
4285  return value_changed;
4286 }

4288 static bool InputFloatN(const char* label, float* v, int components, int decimal_precision)
4289 {
4290  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4291  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4292  if (window->SkipItems)
4293  return false;
4294 
4295  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
4296  const float w_full = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
4297  const float w_item_one = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)((w_full - (style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)) / (float)components));
4298  const float w_item_last = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(w_full - (w_item_one+style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)));
4299 
4300  bool value_changed = false;
4301  ImGui::PushID(label);
4302  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_one);
4303  for (int i = 0; i < components; i++)
4304  {
4305  ImGui::PushID(i);
4306  if (i + 1 == components)
4307  {
4308  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4309  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_last);
4310  }
4311  value_changed |= ImGui::InputFloat("##v", &v[i], 0, 0, decimal_precision);
4312  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4313  ImGui::PopID();
4314  }
4315  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4316  ImGui::PopID();
4317 
4318  ImGui::TextUnformatted(label, FindTextDisplayEnd(label));
4319 
4320  return value_changed;
4321 }

4338 static bool Combo_ArrayGetter(void* data, int idx, const char** out_text)
4339 {
4340  const char** items = (const char**)data;
4341  if (out_text)
4342  *out_text = items[idx];
4343  return true;

4346 // Combo box helper allowing to pass an array of strings.
4347 bool Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, const char** items, int items_count, int popup_height_items)
4348 {
4349  const bool value_changed = Combo(label, current_item, Combo_ArrayGetter, (void*)items, items_count, popup_height_items);
4350  return value_changed;
4351 }
4352 
4353 static bool Combo_StringListGetter(void* data, int idx, const char** out_text)
4354 {
4355  // FIXME-OPT: we could precompute the indices but let's not bother now.
4356  const char* items_separated_by_zeros = (const char*)data;
4357  int items_count = 0;
4358  const char* p = items_separated_by_zeros;
4359  while (*p)
4360  {
4361  if (idx == items_count)
4362  break;
4363  p += strlen(p) + 1;
4364  items_count++;
4365  }
4366  if (!*p)
4367  return false;
4368  if (out_text)
4369  *out_text = p;
4370  return true;
4371 }
4372 
4373 // Combo box helper allowing to pass all items in a single string.
4374 bool Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, const char* items_separated_by_zeros, int popup_height_items)
4375 {
4376  int items_count = 0;
4377  const char* p = items_separated_by_zeros;
4378  while (*p)
4379  {
4380  p += strlen(p) + 1;
4381  items_count++;
4382  }
4383  bool value_changed = Combo(label, current_item, Combo_StringListGetter, (void*)items_separated_by_zeros, items_count, popup_height_items);
4384  return value_changed;
4385 }

4387 // Combo box function.
4388 bool Combo(const char* label, int* current_item, bool (*items_getter)(void*, int, const char**), void* data, int items_count, int popup_height_items)
4389 {
4390  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4391  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4392  if (window->SkipItems)
4393  return false;
4394 
4395  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
4396  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
4397 
4398  const ImVec2 text_size = CalcTextSize(label);
4399  const float arrow_size = (window->FontSize() + style.FramePadding.x * 2.0f);
4400  const ImGuiAabb frame_bb(window->DC.CursorPos, window->DC.CursorPos + ImVec2(window->DC.ItemWidth.back(), text_size.y) + style.FramePadding*2.0f);
4401  const ImGuiAabb bb(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max + ImVec2(style.ItemInnerSpacing.x + text_size.x,0));
4402 
4403  if (ClipAdvance(frame_bb))
4404  return false;
4405 
4406  const bool hovered = (g.HoveredWindow == window) && (g.HoveredId == 0) && IsMouseHoveringBox(bb);
4407 
4408  bool value_changed = false;
4409  ItemSize(frame_bb);
4410  RenderFrame(frame_bb.Min, frame_bb.Max, window->Color(ImGuiCol_FrameBg));
4411  RenderFrame(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x-arrow_size, frame_bb.Min.y), frame_bb.Max, window->Color(hovered ? ImGuiCol_ButtonHovered : ImGuiCol_Button));
4412  RenderCollapseTriangle(ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x-arrow_size, frame_bb.Min.y) + style.FramePadding, true);
4413 
4414  if (*current_item >= 0 && *current_item < items_count)
4415  {
4416  const char* item_text;
4417  if (items_getter(data, *current_item, &item_text))
4418  RenderText(frame_bb.Min + style.FramePadding, item_text, NULL, false);
4419  }
4420 
4421  ImGui::SameLine(0, (int)g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4422  ImGui::TextUnformatted(label, FindTextDisplayEnd(label));
4423 
4424  ImGui::PushID((int)id);
4425  bool menu_toggled = false;
4426  if (hovered)
4427  {
4428  g.HoveredId = id;
4429  if (g.IO.MouseClicked[0])
4430  {
4431  menu_toggled = true;
4432  g.ActiveComboID = (g.ActiveComboID == id) ? 0 : id;
4433  }
4434  }
4435 
4436  if (g.ActiveComboID == id)
4437  {
4438  const ImVec2 backup_pos = ImGui::GetCursorPos();
4439  const float popup_off_x = 0.0f;//g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x;
4440  const float popup_height = (text_size.y + g.Style.ItemSpacing.y) * ImMin(items_count, popup_height_items) + g.Style.WindowPadding.y;
4441  const ImGuiAabb popup_aabb(ImVec2(frame_bb.Min.x+popup_off_x, frame_bb.Max.y), ImVec2(frame_bb.Max.x+popup_off_x, frame_bb.Max.y + popup_height));
4442  ImGui::SetCursorPos(popup_aabb.Min - window->Pos);
4443 
4444  const ImGuiWindowFlags flags = ImGuiWindowFlags_ComboBox | ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders) ? ImGuiWindowFlags_ShowBorders : 0);
4445  ImGui::BeginChild("#ComboBox", popup_aabb.GetSize(), false, flags);
4446  ImGuiWindow* child_window = GetCurrentWindow();
4447  ImGui::Spacing();
4448 
4449  bool combo_item_active = false;
4450  combo_item_active |= (g.ActiveId == child_window->GetID("#SCROLLY"));
4451 
4452  for (int item_idx = 0; item_idx < items_count; item_idx++)
4453  {
4454  const float item_h = child_window->FontSize();
4455  const float spacing_up = (float)(int)(g.Style.ItemSpacing.y/2);
4456  const float spacing_dn = g.Style.ItemSpacing.y - spacing_up;
4457  const ImGuiAabb item_aabb(ImVec2(popup_aabb.Min.x, child_window->DC.CursorPos.y - spacing_up), ImVec2(popup_aabb.Max.x, child_window->DC.CursorPos.y + item_h + spacing_dn));
4458  const ImGuiID item_id = child_window->GetID((void*)(intptr_t)item_idx);
4459 
4460  bool item_hovered, item_held;
4461  bool item_pressed = ButtonBehaviour(item_aabb, item_id, &item_hovered, &item_held, true);
4462  bool item_selected = item_idx == *current_item;
4463 
4464  if (item_hovered || item_selected)
4465  {
4466  const ImU32 col = window->Color((item_held && item_hovered) ? ImGuiCol_HeaderActive : item_hovered ? ImGuiCol_HeaderHovered : ImGuiCol_Header);
4467  RenderFrame(item_aabb.Min, item_aabb.Max, col, false);
4468  }
4469 
4470  const char* item_text;
4471  if (!items_getter(data, item_idx, &item_text))
4472  item_text = "*Unknown item*";
4473  ImGui::Text("%s", item_text);
4474 
4475  if (item_selected)
4476  {
4477  if (menu_toggled)
4478  ImGui::SetScrollPosHere();
4479  }
4480  if (item_pressed)
4481  {
4482  g.ActiveId = 0;
4483  g.ActiveComboID = 0;
4484  value_changed = true;
4485  *current_item = item_idx;
4486  }
4487 
4488  combo_item_active |= (g.ActiveId == item_id);
4489  }
4490  ImGui::EndChild();
4491  ImGui::SetCursorPos(backup_pos);
4492 
4493  if (!combo_item_active && g.ActiveId != 0)
4494  g.ActiveComboID = 0;
4495  }
4496 
4497  ImGui::PopID();
4498 
4499  return value_changed;
4500 }

4548 // Edit colours components color in 0..1 range
4549 // Use CTRL-Click to input value and TAB to go to next item.
4550 bool ColorEdit4(const char* label, float col[4], bool alpha)
4551 {
4552  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4553  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4554  if (window->SkipItems)
4555  return false;
4556 
4557  const ImGuiStyle& style = g.Style;
4558  const ImGuiID id = window->GetID(label);
4559  const float w_full = window->DC.ItemWidth.back();
4560  const float square_sz = (window->FontSize() + style.FramePadding.x * 2.0f);
4561 
4562  ImGuiColorEditMode edit_mode = window->DC.ColorEditMode;
4563  if (edit_mode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelect)
4564  edit_mode = g.ColorEditModeStorage.GetInt(id, 0) % 3;
4565 
4566  float fx = col[0];
4567  float fy = col[1];
4568  float fz = col[2];
4569  float fw = col[3];
4570  const ImVec4 col_display(fx, fy, fz, 1.0f);
4571 
4572  if (edit_mode == ImGuiColorEditMode_HSV)
4573  ImConvertColorRGBtoHSV(fx, fy, fz, fx, fy, fz);
4574 
4575  int ix = (int)(fx * 255.0f + 0.5f);
4576  int iy = (int)(fy * 255.0f + 0.5f);
4577  int iz = (int)(fz * 255.0f + 0.5f);
4578  int iw = (int)(fw * 255.0f + 0.5f);
4579 
4580  int components = alpha ? 4 : 3;
4581  bool value_changed = false;
4582 
4583  ImGui::PushID(label);
4584 
4585  bool hsv = (edit_mode == 1);
4586  switch (edit_mode)
4587  {
4588  case ImGuiColorEditMode_RGB:
4589  case ImGuiColorEditMode_HSV:
4590  {
4591  // 0: RGB 0..255
4592  // 1: HSV 0.255 Sliders
4593  const float w_items_all = w_full - (square_sz + style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4594  const float w_item_one = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)((w_items_all - (style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)) / (float)components));
4595  const float w_item_last = ImMax(1.0f, (float)(int)(w_items_all - (w_item_one+style.FramePadding.x*2.0f+style.ItemInnerSpacing.x) * (components-1)));
4596 
4597  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_one);
4598  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderInt("##X", &ix, 0, 255, hsv ? "H:%3.0f" : "R:%3.0f");
4599  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4600  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderInt("##Y", &iy, 0, 255, hsv ? "S:%3.0f" : "G:%3.0f");
4601  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4602  if (alpha)
4603  {
4604  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderInt("##Z", &iz, 0, 255, hsv ? "V:%3.0f" : "B:%3.0f");
4605  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4606  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_last);
4607  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderInt("##W", &iw, 0, 255, "A:%3.0f");
4608  }
4609  else
4610  {
4611  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_item_last);
4612  value_changed |= ImGui::SliderInt("##Z", &iz, 0, 255, hsv ? "V:%3.0f" : "B:%3.0f");
4613  }
4614  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4615  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4616  }
4617  break;
4618  case ImGuiColorEditMode_HEX:
4619  {
4620  // 2: RGB Hexadecimal
4621  const float w_slider_all = w_full - square_sz;
4622  char buf[64];
4623  if (alpha)
4624  sprintf(buf, "#%02X%02X%02X%02X", ix, iy, iz, iw);
4625  else
4626  sprintf(buf, "#%02X%02X%02X", ix, iy, iz);
4627  ImGui::PushItemWidth(w_slider_all - g.Style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4628  value_changed |= ImGui::InputText("##Text", buf, IM_ARRAYSIZE(buf), ImGuiInputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal);
4629  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4630  char* p = buf;
4631  while (*p == '#' || *p == ' ' || *p == '\t')
4632  p++;
4633  ix = iy = iz = iw = 0;
4634  if (alpha)
4635  sscanf(p, "%02X%02X%02X%02X", &ix, &iy, &iz, &iw);
4636  else
4637  sscanf(p, "%02X%02X%02X", &ix, &iy, &iz);
4638  }
4639  break;
4640  }
4641 
4642  ImGui::SameLine(0, 0);
4643  ImGui::ColorButton(col_display);
4644 
4645  if (window->DC.ColorEditMode == ImGuiColorEditMode_UserSelect)
4646  {
4647  ImGui::SameLine(0, (int)style.ItemInnerSpacing.x);
4648  const char* button_titles[3] = { "RGB", "HSV", "HEX" };
4649  if (ImGui::Button(button_titles[edit_mode]))
4650  {
4651  // Don't set 'edit_mode' right away!
4652  g.ColorEditModeStorage.SetInt(id, (edit_mode + 1) % 3);
4653  }
4654  }
4655 
4656  ImGui::SameLine();
4657  ImGui::TextUnformatted(label, FindTextDisplayEnd(label));
4658 
4659  // Convert back
4660  fx = ix / 255.0f;
4661  fy = iy / 255.0f;
4662  fz = iz / 255.0f;
4663  fw = iw / 255.0f;
4664  if (edit_mode == 1)
4665  ImConvertColorHSVtoRGB(fx, fy, fz, fx, fy, fz);
4666 
4667  if (value_changed)
4668  {
4669  col[0] = fx;
4670  col[1] = fy;
4671  col[2] = fz;
4672  if (alpha)
4673  col[3] = fw;
4674  }
4675 
4676  ImGui::PopID();
4677 
4678  return value_changed;
4679 }

4723 static void ItemSize(ImVec2 size, ImVec2* adjust_start_offset)
4724 {
4725  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4726  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4727  if (window->SkipItems)
4728  return;
4729 
4730  const float line_height = ImMax(window->DC.CurrentLineHeight, size.y);
4731  if (adjust_start_offset)
4732  adjust_start_offset->y = adjust_start_offset->y + (line_height - size.y) * 0.5f;
4733 
4734  // Always align ourselves on pixel boundaries
4735  window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine = ImVec2(window->DC.CursorPos.x + size.x, window->DC.CursorPos.y);
4736  window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2((float)(int)(window->Pos.x + window->DC.ColumnStartX), (float)(int)(window->DC.CursorPos.y + line_height + g.Style.ItemSpacing.y));
4737 
4738  window->SizeContentsFit = ImMax(window->SizeContentsFit, ImVec2(window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.x, window->DC.CursorPos.y) - window->Pos + ImVec2(0.0f, window->ScrollY));
4739 
4740  window->DC.PrevLineHeight = line_height;
4741  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = 0.0f;
4742 }
4743

4745 {
4746  ItemSize(aabb.GetSize(), adjust_start_offset);
4747 }

4749 void NextColumn()
4750 {
4751  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4752  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4753  if (window->SkipItems)
4754  return;
4755 
4756  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount > 1)

4759  ImGui::PopClipRect();
4760  if (++window->DC.ColumnCurrent < window->DC.ColumnsCount)
4761  SameLine((int)(ImGui::GetColumnOffset(window->DC.ColumnCurrent) + g.Style.ItemSpacing.x));
4762  else
4763  window->DC.ColumnCurrent = 0;
4764  ImGui::PushColumnClipRect();
4765  ImGui::PushItemWidth(ImGui::GetColumnWidth() * 0.65f);
4766  }
4767 }

4785 static bool ClipAdvance(const ImGuiAabb& bb)
4786 {
4787  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4788  window->DC.LastItemAabb = bb;
4789  if (ImGui::IsClipped(bb))
4790  {
4791  window->DC.LastItemHovered = false;
4792  return true;
4793  }
4794  window->DC.LastItemHovered = ImGui::IsMouseHoveringBox(bb); // this is a sensible default but widgets are free to override it after calling ClipAdvance
4795  return false;
4796 }
4797 
4798 // Gets back to previous line and continue with horizontal layout
4799 // column_x == 0 : follow on previous item
4800 // columm_x != 0 : align to specified column
4801 // spacing_w < 0 : use default spacing if column_x==0, no spacing if column_x!=0
4802 // spacing_w >= 0 : enforce spacing
4803 void SameLine(int column_x, int spacing_w)
4804 {
4805  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4806  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4807  if (window->SkipItems)
4808  return;
4809 
4810  float x, y;
4811  if (column_x != 0)
4812  {
4813  if (spacing_w < 0) spacing_w = 0;
4814  x = window->Pos.x + (float)column_x + (float)spacing_w;
4815  y = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.y;
4816  }
4817  else
4818  {
4819  if (spacing_w < 0) spacing_w = (int)g.Style.ItemSpacing.x;
4820  x = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.x + (float)spacing_w;
4821  y = window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine.y;
4822  }
4823  window->DC.CurrentLineHeight = window->DC.PrevLineHeight;
4824  window->DC.CursorPos = ImVec2(x, y);
4825 }
4826 
4827 float GetColumnOffset(int column_index)
4828 {
4829  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4830  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4831  if (column_index < 0)
4832  column_index = window->DC.ColumnCurrent;
4833 
4834  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetID + ImGuiID(column_index);
4835  RegisterAliveId(column_id);
4836  const float default_t = column_index / (float)window->DC.ColumnsCount;
4837  const float t = (float)window->StateStorage.GetInt(column_id, (int)(default_t * 8096)) / 8096; // Cheaply store our floating point value inside the integer (could store an union into the map?)
4838 
4839  const float offset = window->DC.ColumnStartX + t * (window->Size.x - g.Style.ScrollBarWidth - window->DC.ColumnStartX);
4840  return offset;
4841 }
4842 
4843 void SetColumnOffset(int column_index, float offset)
4844 {

4847  if (column_index < 0)
4848  column_index = window->DC.ColumnCurrent;
4849 
4850  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetID + ImGuiID(column_index);
4851  const float t = (offset - window->DC.ColumnStartX) / (window->Size.x - g.Style.ScrollBarWidth - window->DC.ColumnStartX);
4852  window->StateStorage.SetInt(column_id, (int)(t*8096));
4853 }

4855 float GetColumnWidth(int column_index)

4859  column_index = window->DC.ColumnCurrent;
4860

4876 void Columns(int columns_count, const char* id, bool border)
4877 {
4878  ImGuiState& g = GImGui;
4879  ImGuiWindow* window = GetCurrentWindow();
4880  if (window->SkipItems)
4881  return;
4882 
4883  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1)
4884  {
4885  if (window->DC.ColumnCurrent != 0)
4886  ImGui::ItemSize(ImVec2(0,0)); // Advance to column 0
4887  ImGui::PopItemWidth();
4888  ImGui::PopClipRect();
4889  }
4890 
4891  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != columns_count && window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1 && window->DC.ColumnsShowBorders)
4892  {
4893  // Draw columns and handle resize
4894  const float y1 = window->DC.ColumnsStartCursorPos.y;
4895  const float y2 = window->DC.CursorPos.y;
4896  for (int i = 1; i < window->DC.ColumnsCount; i++)
4897  {
4898  float x = window->Pos.x + GetColumnOffset(i);
4899 
4900  const ImGuiID column_id = window->DC.ColumnsSetID + ImGuiID(i);
4901  const ImGuiAabb column_aabb(ImVec2(x-4,y1),ImVec2(x+4,y2));
4902 
4903  if (IsClipped(column_aabb))
4904  continue;
4905 
4906  bool hovered, held;
4907  ButtonBehaviour(column_aabb, column_id, &hovered, &held, true);
4908 
4909  // Draw before resize so our items positioning are in sync with the line being drawn
4910  const ImU32 col = window->Color(held ? ImGuiCol_ColumnActive : hovered ? ImGuiCol_ColumnHovered : ImGuiCol_Column);
4911  const float xi = (float)(int)x;
4912  window->DrawList->AddLine(ImVec2(xi, y1), ImVec2(xi, y2), col);
4913 
4914  if (held)
4915  {
4916  x -= window->Pos.x;
4917  x = ImClamp(x + g.IO.MouseDelta.x, ImGui::GetColumnOffset(i-1)+g.Style.ColumnsMinSpacing, ImGui::GetColumnOffset(i+1)-g.Style.ColumnsMinSpacing);
4918  SetColumnOffset(i, x);
4919  x += window->Pos.x;
4920  }
4921  }
4922  }
4923 
4924  window->DC.ColumnsSetID = window->GetID(id ? id : "");
4925  window->DC.ColumnCurrent = 0;
4926  window->DC.ColumnsCount = columns_count;
4927  window->DC.ColumnsShowBorders = border;
4928  window->DC.ColumnsStartCursorPos = window->DC.CursorPos;
4929 
4930  if (window->DC.ColumnsCount != 1)
4931  {
4932  ImGui::PushColumnClipRect();
4933  ImGui::PushItemWidth(ImGui::GetColumnWidth() * 0.65f);
4934  }
4935 }

5022 void ImDrawList::Clear()
5023 {
5024  commands.resize(0);
5025  vtx_buffer.resize(0);
5026  vtx_write = NULL;
5027  clip_rect_stack.resize(0);
5028 }
5029 
5030 void ImDrawList::PushClipRect(const ImVec4& clip_rect)
5031 {
5032  if (!commands.empty() && commands.back().vtx_count == 0)
5033  {
5034  // Reuse empty command because high-level clipping may have discarded the other vertices already
5035  commands.back().clip_rect = clip_rect;
5036  }
5037  else
5038  {
5039  ImDrawCmd draw_cmd;
5040  draw_cmd.vtx_count = 0;
5041  draw_cmd.clip_rect = clip_rect;
5042  commands.push_back(draw_cmd);
5043  }
5044  clip_rect_stack.push_back(clip_rect);
5045 }
5046 
5047 void ImDrawList::PopClipRect()
5048 {
5049  clip_rect_stack.pop_back();
5050  const ImVec4 clip_rect = clip_rect_stack.empty() ? ImVec4(-9999.0f,-9999.0f, +9999.0f, +9999.0f) : clip_rect_stack.back();
5051  if (!commands.empty() && commands.back().vtx_count == 0)
5052  {
5053  // Reuse empty command because high-level clipping may have discarded the other vertices already
5054  commands.back().clip_rect = clip_rect;
5055  }
5056  else
5057  {
5058  ImDrawCmd draw_cmd;
5059  draw_cmd.vtx_count = 0;
5060  draw_cmd.clip_rect = clip_rect;
5061  commands.push_back(draw_cmd);
5062  }
5063 }
5064 
5065 void ImDrawList::ReserveVertices(unsigned int vtx_count)
5066 {
5067  if (vtx_count > 0)
5068  {
5069  ImDrawCmd& draw_cmd = commands.back();
5070  draw_cmd.vtx_count += vtx_count;
5071  vtx_buffer.resize(vtx_buffer.size() + vtx_count);
5072  vtx_write = &vtx_buffer[vtx_buffer.size() - vtx_count];
5073  }
5074 }
5075 
5076 void ImDrawList::AddVtx(const ImVec2& pos, ImU32 col)
5077 {
5078  vtx_write->pos = pos;
5079  vtx_write->col = col;
5080  vtx_write->uv = GImGui.IO.FontTexUvForWhite;
5081  vtx_write++;
5082 }
5083 
5084 void ImDrawList::AddVtxLine(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, ImU32 col)
5085 {
5086  const float offset = GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset;
5087  const ImVec2 hn = (b - a) * (0.50f / ImLength(b - a)); // half normal
5088  const ImVec2 hp0 = ImVec2(offset - hn.y, offset + hn.x); // half perpendiculars + user offset
5089  const ImVec2 hp1 = ImVec2(offset + hn.y, offset - hn.x);
5090 
5091  // Two triangles makes up one line. Using triangles allows us to make draw calls.
5092  AddVtx(a + hp0, col);
5093  AddVtx(b + hp0, col);
5094  AddVtx(a + hp1, col);
5095  AddVtx(b + hp0, col);
5096  AddVtx(b + hp1, col);
5097  AddVtx(a + hp1, col);
5098 }
5099 
5100 void ImDrawList::AddLine(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, ImU32 col)
5101 {
5102  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5103  return;
5104 
5105  ReserveVertices(6);
5106  AddVtxLine(a, b, col);
5107 }
5108 
5109 void ImDrawList::AddArc(const ImVec2& center, float rad, ImU32 col, int a_min, int a_max, bool tris, const ImVec2& third_point_offset)
5110 {
5111  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5112  return;
5113 
5114  static ImVec2 circle_vtx[12];
5115  static bool circle_vtx_builds = false;
5116  if (!circle_vtx_builds)
5117  {
5118  for (int i = 0; i < IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx); i++)
5119  {
5120  const float a = ((float)i / (float)IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx)) * 2*PI;
5121  circle_vtx[i].x = cos(a + PI);
5122  circle_vtx[i].y = sin(a + PI);
5123  }
5124  circle_vtx_builds = true;
5125  }
5126 
5127  if (tris)
5128  {
5129  ReserveVertices((unsigned int)(a_max-a_min) * 3);
5130  for (int a = a_min; a < a_max; a++)
5131  {
5132  AddVtx(center + circle_vtx[a % IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx)] * rad, col);
5133  AddVtx(center + circle_vtx[(a+1) % IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx)] * rad, col);
5134  AddVtx(center + third_point_offset, col);
5135  }
5136  }
5137  else
5138  {
5139  ReserveVertices((unsigned int)(a_max-a_min) * 6);
5140  for (int a = a_min; a < a_max; a++)
5141  AddVtxLine(center + circle_vtx[a % IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx)] * rad, center + circle_vtx[(a+1) % IM_ARRAYSIZE(circle_vtx)] * rad, col);
5142  }
5143 }
5144 
5145 void ImDrawList::AddRect(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, ImU32 col, float rounding, int rounding_corners)
5146 {
5147  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5148  return;
5149 
5150  //const float r = ImMin(rounding, ImMin(fabsf(b.x-a.x), fabsf(b.y-a.y))*0.5f);
5151  float r = rounding;
5152  r = ImMin(r, fabsf(b.x-a.x) * ( ((rounding_corners&(1|2))==(1|2)) || ((rounding_corners&(4|8))==(4|8)) ? 0.5f : 1.0f ));
5153  r = ImMin(r, fabsf(b.y-a.y) * ( ((rounding_corners&(1|8))==(1|8)) || ((rounding_corners&(2|4))==(2|4)) ? 0.5f : 1.0f ));
5154 
5155  if (r == 0.0f || rounding_corners == 0)
5156  {
5157  ReserveVertices(4*6);
5158  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(a.x,a.y), ImVec2(b.x,a.y), col);
5159  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(b.x,a.y), ImVec2(b.x,b.y), col);
5160  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(b.x,b.y), ImVec2(a.x,b.y), col);
5161  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(a.x,b.y), ImVec2(a.x,a.y), col);
5162  }
5163  else
5164  {
5165  ReserveVertices(4*6);
5166  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(a.x + ((rounding_corners & 1)?r:0), a.y), ImVec2(b.x - ((rounding_corners & 2)?r:0), a.y), col);
5167  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(b.x, a.y + ((rounding_corners & 2)?r:0)), ImVec2(b.x, b.y - ((rounding_corners & 4)?r:0)), col);
5168  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(b.x - ((rounding_corners & 4)?r:0), b.y), ImVec2(a.x + ((rounding_corners & 8)?r:0), b.y), col);
5169  AddVtxLine(ImVec2(a.x, b.y - ((rounding_corners & 8)?r:0)), ImVec2(a.x, a.y + ((rounding_corners & 1)?r:0)), col);
5170 
5171  if (rounding_corners & 1) AddArc(ImVec2(a.x+r,a.y+r), r, col, 0, 3);
5172  if (rounding_corners & 2) AddArc(ImVec2(b.x-r,a.y+r), r, col, 3, 6);
5173  if (rounding_corners & 4) AddArc(ImVec2(b.x-r,b.y-r), r, col, 6, 9);
5174  if (rounding_corners & 8) AddArc(ImVec2(a.x+r,b.y-r), r, col, 9, 12);
5175  }
5176 }
5177 
5178 void ImDrawList::AddRectFilled(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, ImU32 col, float rounding, int rounding_corners)
5179 {
5180  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5181  return;
5182 
5183  //const float r = ImMin(rounding, ImMin(fabsf(b.x-a.x), fabsf(b.y-a.y))*0.5f);
5184  float r = rounding;
5185  r = ImMin(r, fabsf(b.x-a.x) * ( ((rounding_corners&(1|2))==(1|2)) || ((rounding_corners&(4|8))==(4|8)) ? 0.5f : 1.0f ));
5186  r = ImMin(r, fabsf(b.y-a.y) * ( ((rounding_corners&(1|8))==(1|8)) || ((rounding_corners&(2|4))==(2|4)) ? 0.5f : 1.0f ));
5187 
5188  if (r == 0.0f || rounding_corners == 0)
5189  {
5190  // Use triangle so we can merge more draw calls together (at the cost of extra vertices)
5191  ReserveVertices(6);
5192  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,a.y), col);
5193  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,a.y), col);
5194  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,b.y), col);
5195  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,a.y), col);
5196  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,b.y), col);
5197  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,b.y), col);
5198  }
5199  else
5200  {
5201  ReserveVertices(6+6*2);
5202  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,a.y), col);
5203  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,a.y), col);
5204  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,b.y), col);
5205  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,a.y), col);
5206  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,b.y), col);
5207  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,b.y), col);
5208 
5209  float top_y = (rounding_corners & 1) ? a.y+r : a.y;
5210  float bot_y = (rounding_corners & 8) ? b.y-r : b.y;
5211  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,top_y), col);
5212  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,top_y), col);
5213  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,bot_y), col);
5214  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,top_y), col);
5215  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x+r,bot_y), col);
5216  AddVtx(ImVec2(a.x,bot_y), col);
5217 
5218  top_y = (rounding_corners & 2) ? a.y+r : a.y;
5219  bot_y = (rounding_corners & 4) ? b.y-r : b.y;
5220  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,top_y), col);
5221  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,top_y), col);
5222  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,bot_y), col);
5223  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,top_y), col);
5224  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x,bot_y), col);
5225  AddVtx(ImVec2(b.x-r,bot_y), col);
5226 
5227  if (rounding_corners & 1) AddArc(ImVec2(a.x+r,a.y+r), r, col, 0, 3, true);
5228  if (rounding_corners & 2) AddArc(ImVec2(b.x-r,a.y+r), r, col, 3, 6, true);
5229  if (rounding_corners & 4) AddArc(ImVec2(b.x-r,b.y-r), r, col, 6, 9, true);
5230  if (rounding_corners & 8) AddArc(ImVec2(a.x+r,b.y-r), r, col, 9, 12,true);
5231  }
5232 }
5233 
5234 void ImDrawList::AddTriangleFilled(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& c, ImU32 col)
5235 {
5236  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5237  return;
5238 
5239  const ImVec2 offset(GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset,GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset);
5240 
5241  ReserveVertices(3);
5242  AddVtx(a + offset, col);
5243  AddVtx(b + offset, col);
5244  AddVtx(c + offset, col);
5245 }

5247 void ImDrawList::AddCircle(const ImVec2& centre, float radius, ImU32 col, int num_segments)
5248 {
5249  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5250  return;
5251 
5252  const ImVec2 offset(GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset,GImGui.IO.PixelCenterOffset);
5253 
5254  ReserveVertices((unsigned int)num_segments*6);
5255  const float a_step = 2*PI/(float)num_segments;
5256  float a0 = 0.0f;
5257  for (int i = 0; i < num_segments; i++)
5258  {
5259  const float a1 = (i + 1) == num_segments ? 0.0f : a0 + a_step;
5260  AddVtxLine(centre + offset + ImVec2(cos(a0),sin(a0))*radius, centre + ImVec2(cos(a1),sin(a1))*radius, col);
5261  a0 = a1;
5262  }

5285 void ImDrawList::AddText(ImFont font, float font_size, const ImVec2& pos, ImU32 col, const char* text_begin, const char* text_end)
5286 {
5287  if ((col >> 24) == 0)
5288  return;
5289 
5290  if (text_end == NULL)
5291  text_end = text_begin + strlen(text_begin);
5292 
5293  // reserve vertices for worse case
5294  const unsigned int char_count = (unsigned int)(text_end - text_begin);
5295  const unsigned int vtx_count_max = char_count * 6;
5296  const size_t vtx_begin = vtx_buffer.size();
5297  ReserveVertices(vtx_count_max);
5298 
5299  font->RenderText(font_size, pos, col, clip_rect_stack.back(), text_begin, text_end, vtx_write);
5300 
5301  // give back unused vertices
5302  vtx_buffer.resize((size_t)(vtx_write - &vtx_buffer.front()));
5303  const size_t vtx_count = vtx_buffer.size() - vtx_begin;
5304  commands.back().vtx_count -= (unsigned int)(vtx_count_max - vtx_count);
5305  vtx_write -= (vtx_count_max - vtx_count);
5306 }

5340 bool ImBitmapFont::LoadFromFile(const char* filename)
5341 {
5342  IM_ASSERT(!IsLoaded()); // Call Clear()
5343 
5344  // Load file
5345  FILE* f;
5346  if ((f = fopen(filename, "rb")) == NULL)
5347  return false;
5348  if (fseek(f, 0, SEEK_END))
5349  {
5350  fclose(f);
5351  return false;
5352  }
5353  const long f_size = ftell(f);
5354  if (f_size == -1)
5355  {
5356  fclose(f);
5357  return false;
5358  }
5359  DataSize = (size_t)f_size;
5360  if (fseek(f, 0, SEEK_SET))
5361  {
5362  fclose(f);
5363  return false;
5364  }
5365  if ((Data = (unsigned char*)ImGui::MemAlloc(DataSize)) == NULL)
5366  {
5367  fclose(f);
5368  return false;
5369  }
5370  if (fread(Data, 1, DataSize, f) != DataSize)
5371  {
5372  fclose(f);
5373  ImGui::MemFree(Data);
5374  return false;
5375  }
5376  fclose(f);
5377  DataOwned = true;
5378  return LoadFromMemory(Data, DataSize);
5379 }
5380 
5381 bool ImBitmapFont::LoadFromMemory(const void* data, size_t data_size)
5382 {
5383  IM_ASSERT(!IsLoaded()); // Call Clear()
5384 
5385  Data = (unsigned char*)data;
5386  DataSize = data_size;
5387 
5388  // Parse data
5389  if (DataSize < 4 || Data[0] != 'B' || Data[1] != 'M' || Data[2] != 'F' || Data[3] != 0x03)
5390  return false;
5391  for (const unsigned char* p = Data+4; p < Data + DataSize; )
5392  {
5393  const unsigned char block_type = *(unsigned char*)p;
5394  p += sizeof(unsigned char);
5395  const ImU32 block_size = *(ImU32*)p;
5396  p += sizeof(ImU32);
5397 
5398  switch (block_type)
5399  {
5400  case 1:
5401  IM_ASSERT(Info == NULL);
5402  Info = (FntInfo*)p;
5403  break;
5404  case 2:
5405  IM_ASSERT(Common == NULL);
5406  Common = (FntCommon*)p;
5407  break;
5408  case 3:
5409  for (const unsigned char* s = p; s < p+block_size && s < Data+DataSize; s = s + strlen((const char*)s) + 1)
5410  Filenames.push_back((const char*)s);
5411  break;
5412  case 4:
5413  IM_ASSERT(Glyphs == NULL && GlyphsCount == 0);
5414  Glyphs = (FntGlyph*)p;
5415  GlyphsCount = block_size / sizeof(FntGlyph);
5416  break;
5417  default:
5418  IM_ASSERT(Kerning == NULL && KerningCount == 0);
5419  Kerning = (FntKerning*)p;
5420  KerningCount = block_size / sizeof(FntKerning);
5421  break;
5422  }
5423  p += block_size;
5424  }
5425 
5426  BuildLookupTable();
5427  return true;
5428 }
5429 
5430 void ImBitmapFont::BuildLookupTable()
5431 {
5432  ImU32 max_c = 0;
5433  for (size_t i = 0; i != GlyphsCount; i++)
5434  if (max_c < Glyphs[i].Id)
5435  max_c = Glyphs[i].Id;
5436 
5437  IndexLookup.clear();
5438  IndexLookup.resize(max_c + 1);
5439  for (size_t i = 0; i < IndexLookup.size(); i++)
5440  IndexLookup[i] = -1;
5441  for (size_t i = 0; i < GlyphsCount; i++)
5442  IndexLookup[Glyphs[i].Id] = (int)i;
5443 }
5444 
5445 const ImBitmapFont::FntGlyph* ImBitmapFont::FindGlyph(unsigned short c) const
5446 {
5447  if (c < (int)IndexLookup.size())
5448  {
5449  const int i = IndexLookup[c];
5450  if (i >= 0 && i < (int)GlyphsCount)
5451  return &Glyphs[i];
5452  }
5453  return NULL;
5454 }
5455 
5456 // Convert UTF-8 to 32-bits character, process single character input.
5457 // Based on stb_from_utf8() from github.com/nothings/stb/
5458 static int ImTextCharFromUtf8(unsigned int* out_char, const char* in_text, const char* in_text_end)
5459 {
5460  if (*in_text != 0)
5461  {
5462  unsigned int c = -1;
5463  const unsigned char* str = (const unsigned char*)in_text;
5464  if (!(*str & 0x80))
5465  {
5466  c = (unsigned int)(*str++);
5467  *out_char = c;
5468  return 1;
5469  }
5470  if ((*str & 0xe0) == 0xc0)
5471  {
5472  if (in_text_end && in_text_end - (const char*)str < 2) return -1;
5473  if (*str < 0xc2) return -1;
5474  c = (*str++ & 0x1f) << 6;
5475  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5476  c += (*str++ & 0x3f);
5477  *out_char = c;
5478  return 2;
5479  }
5480  if ((*str & 0xf0) == 0xe0)
5481  {
5482  if (in_text_end && in_text_end - (const char*)str < 3) return -1;
5483  if (*str == 0xe0 && (str[1] < 0xa0 || str[1] > 0xbf)) return -1;
5484  if (*str == 0xed && str[1] > 0x9f) return -1; // str[1] < 0x80 is checked below
5485  c = (*str++ & 0x0f) << 12;
5486  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5487  c += (*str++ & 0x3f) << 6;
5488  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5489  c += (*str++ & 0x3f);
5490  *out_char = c;
5491  return 3;
5492  }
5493  if ((*str & 0xf8) == 0xf0)
5494  {
5495  if (in_text_end && in_text_end - (const char*)str < 4) return -1;
5496  if (*str > 0xf4) return -1;
5497  if (*str == 0xf0 && (str[1] < 0x90 || str[1] > 0xbf)) return -1;
5498  if (*str == 0xf4 && str[1] > 0x8f) return -1; // str[1] < 0x80 is checked below
5499  c = (*str++ & 0x07) << 18;
5500  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5501  c += (*str++ & 0x3f) << 12;
5502  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5503  c += (*str++ & 0x3f) << 6;
5504  if ((*str & 0xc0) != 0x80) return -1;
5505  c += (*str++ & 0x3f);
5506  // utf-8 encodings of values used in surrogate pairs are invalid
5507  if ((c & 0xFFFFF800) == 0xD800) return -1;
5508  *out_char = c;
5509  return 4;
5510  }
5511  }
5512  *out_char = 0;
5513  return 0;
5514 }
5515 
5516 static int ImTextStrFromUtf8(ImWchar* buf, size_t buf_size, const char* in_text, const char* in_text_end)
5517 {
5518  ImWchar* buf_out = buf;
5519  ImWchar* buf_end = buf + buf_size;
5520  while (buf_out < buf_end-1 && (!in_text_end || in_text < in_text_end) && *in_text)
5521  {
5522  unsigned int c;
5523  in_text += ImTextCharFromUtf8(&c, in_text, in_text_end);
5524  if (c < 0x10000) // FIXME: Losing characters that don't fit in 2 bytes
5525  *buf_out++ = (ImWchar)c;
5526  }
5527  *buf_out = 0;
5528  return buf_out - buf;
5529 }
5530 
5531 // Based on stb_to_utf8() from github.com/nothings/stb/
5532 static int ImTextCharToUtf8(char* buf, size_t buf_size, unsigned int c)
5533 {
5534  if (c)
5535  {
5536  int i = 0;
5537  int n = (size_t)buf_size;
5538  if (c < 0x80)
5539  {
5540  if (i+1 > n) return 0;
5541  buf[i++] = (char)c;
5542  return 1;
5543  }
5544  else if (c < 0x800)
5545  {
5546  if (i+2 > n) return 0;
5547  buf[i++] = 0xc0 + (c >> 6);
5548  buf[i++] = 0x80 + (c & 0x3f);
5549  return 2;
5550  }
5551  else if (c >= 0xdc00 && c < 0xe000)
5552  {
5553  return 0;
5554  }
5555  else if (c >= 0xd800 && c < 0xdc00)
5556  {
5557  if (i+4 > n) return 0;
5558  buf[i++] = 0xf0 + (c >> 18);
5559  buf[i++] = 0x80 + ((c >> 12) & 0x3f);
5560  buf[i++] = 0x80 + ((c >> 6) & 0x3f);
5561  buf[i++] = 0x80 + ((c ) & 0x3f);
5562  return 4;
5563  }
5564  //else if (c < 0x10000)
5565  {
5566  if (i+3 > n) return 0;
5567  buf[i++] = 0xe0 + (c >> 12);
5568  buf[i++] = 0x80 + ((c>> 6) & 0x3f);
5569  buf[i++] = 0x80 + ((c ) & 0x3f);
5570  return 3;
5571  }
5572  }
5573  return 0;
5574 }
5575 
5576 static int ImTextStrToUtf8(char* buf, size_t buf_size, const ImWchar* in_text, const ImWchar* in_text_end)
5577 {
5578  char* buf_out = buf;
5579  const char* buf_end = buf + buf_size;
5580  while (buf_out < buf_end-1 && (!in_text_end || in_text < in_text_end) && *in_text)
5581  {
5582  buf_out += ImTextCharToUtf8(buf_out, buf_end-buf_out-1, (unsigned int)*in_text);
5583  in_text++;
5584  }
5585  *buf_out = 0;
5586  return buf_out - buf;
5587 }
5588 
5589 ImVec2 ImBitmapFont::CalcTextSizeA(float size, float max_width, const char* text_begin, const char* text_end, const char** remaining) const
5590 {
5591  if (max_width == 0.0f)
5592  max_width = FLT_MAX;
5593  if (!text_end)
5594  text_end = text_begin + strlen(text_begin);
5595 
5596  const float scale = size / (float)Info->FontSize;
5597  const float line_height = (float)Info->FontSize * scale;
5598  const FntGlyph* fallback_glyph = FindGlyph(GImGui.IO.FontFallbackGlyph);
5599 
5600  ImVec2 text_size = ImVec2(0,0);
5601  float line_width = 0.0f;
5602 
5603  const char* s = text_begin;
5604  while (s < text_end)
5605  {
5606  unsigned int c;
5607  const int bytes_count = ImTextCharFromUtf8(&c, s, text_end);
5608  s += bytes_count > 0 ? bytes_count : 1; // Handle decoding failure by skipping to next byte
5609 
5610  if (c == '\n')
5611  {
5612  if (text_size.x < line_width)
5613  text_size.x = line_width;
5614  text_size.y += line_height;
5615  line_width = 0;
5616  }
5617  else if (c == '\t')
5618  {
5619  // FIXME: Better TAB handling needed.
5620  if (const FntGlyph* glyph = FindGlyph((unsigned short)' '))
5621  line_width += (glyph->XAdvance + Info->SpacingHoriz) * 4 * scale;
5622  }
5623  else
5624  {
5625  const FntGlyph* glyph = FindGlyph((unsigned short)c);
5626  if (!glyph)
5627  glyph = fallback_glyph;
5628  if (glyph)
5629  {
5630  const float char_width = (glyph->XAdvance + Info->SpacingHoriz) * scale;
5631  //const float char_extend = (glyph->XOffset + glyph->Width * scale);
5632  if (line_width + char_width >= max_width)
5633  break;
5634  line_width += char_width;
5635  }
5636  }
5637  }
5638 
5639  if (line_width > 0 || text_size.y == 0.0f)
5640  {
5641  if (text_size.x < line_width)
5642  text_size.x = line_width;
5643  text_size.y += line_height;
5644  }
5645 
5646  if (remaining)
5647  *remaining = s;
5648 
5649  return text_size;
5650 }
