5712 
5713 void ImBitmapFont::RenderText(float size, ImVec2 pos, ImU32 col, const ImVec4& clip_rect_ref, const char* text_begin, const char* text_end, ImDrawVert*& out_vertices) const
5714 {
5715  if (!text_end)
5716  text_end = text_begin + strlen(text_begin);
5717 
5718  const float line_height = (float)Info->FontSize;
5719  const float scale = size / (float)Info->FontSize;
5720  const float tex_scale_x = 1.0f / (float)Common->ScaleW;
5721  const float tex_scale_y = 1.0f / (float)(Common->ScaleH);
5722  const float outline = (float)Info->Outline;
5723  const FntGlyph* fallback_glyph = FindGlyph(GImGui.IO.FontFallbackGlyph);
5724 
5725  // Align to be pixel perfect
5726  pos.x = (float)(int)pos.x;
5727  pos.y = (float)(int)pos.y + GImGui.IO.FontYOffset;
5728 
5729  const ImVec4 clip_rect = clip_rect_ref;
5730 
5731  float x = pos.x;
5732  float y = pos.y;
5733  for (const char* s = text_begin; s < text_end; )
5734  {
5735  unsigned int c;
5736  const int bytes_count = ImTextCharFromUtf8(&c, s, text_end);
5737  s += bytes_count > 0 ? bytes_count : 1; // Handle decoding failure by skipping to next byte
5738  if (c >= 0x10000)
5739  continue;
5740 
5741  if (c == '\n')
5742  {
5743  x = pos.x;
5744  y += line_height * scale;
5745  continue;
5746  }
5747 
5748  const FntGlyph* glyph = FindGlyph((unsigned short)c);
5749  if (!glyph)
5750  glyph = fallback_glyph;
5751  if (glyph)
5752  {
5753  const float char_width = (glyph->XAdvance + Info->SpacingHoriz) * scale;
5754  //const float char_extend = (glyph->XOffset + glyph->Width * scale);
5755 
5756  if (c != ' ' && c != '\n')
5757  {
5758  // Clipping due to Y limits is more likely
5759  const float y1 = (float)(y + (glyph->YOffset + outline*2) * scale);
5760  const float y2 = (float)(y1 + glyph->Height * scale);
5761  if (y1 > clip_rect.w || y2 < clip_rect.y)
5762  {
5763  x += char_width;
5764  continue;
5765  }
5766 
5767  const float x1 = (float)(x + (glyph->XOffset + outline) * scale);
5768  const float x2 = (float)(x1 + glyph->Width * scale);
5769  if (x1 > clip_rect.z || x2 < clip_rect.x)
5770  {
5771  x += char_width;
5772  continue;
5773  }
5774 
5775  const float s1 = (glyph->X) * tex_scale_x;
5776  const float t1 = (glyph->Y) * tex_scale_y;
5777  const float s2 = (glyph->X + glyph->Width) * tex_scale_x;
5778  const float t2 = (glyph->Y + glyph->Height) * tex_scale_y;
5779 
5780  out_vertices[0].pos = ImVec2(x1, y1);
5781  out_vertices[0].uv = ImVec2(s1, t1);
5782  out_vertices[0].col = col;
5783 
5784  out_vertices[1].pos = ImVec2(x2, y1);
5785  out_vertices[1].uv = ImVec2(s2, t1);
5786  out_vertices[1].col = col;
5787 
5788  out_vertices[2].pos = ImVec2(x2, y2);
5789  out_vertices[2].uv = ImVec2(s2, t2);
5790  out_vertices[2].col = col;
5791 
5792  out_vertices[3] = out_vertices[0];
5793  out_vertices[4] = out_vertices[2];
5794 
5795  out_vertices[5].pos = ImVec2(x1, y2);
5796  out_vertices[5].uv = ImVec2(s1, t2);
5797  out_vertices[5].col = col;
5798 
5799  out_vertices += 6;
5800  }
5801 
5802  x += char_width;
5803  }
5804  else if (c == '\t')
5805  {
5806  if (const FntGlyph* glyph = FindGlyph((unsigned short)' '))
5807  x += (glyph->XAdvance + Info->SpacingHoriz) * 4 * scale;
5808  }
5809  }
5810 }

5813 // PLATFORM DEPENDANT HELPERS
5814 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5815 
5816 #if defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(IMGUI_DISABLE_WIN32_DEFAULT_CLIPBOARD_FUNCS)
5817 
5818 #define WIN32_LEAN_AND_MEAN
5819 #include <windows.h>
5820 
5821 // Win32 API clipboard implementation
5822 static const char* GetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl()
5823 {
5824  static char* buf_local = NULL;
5825  if (buf_local)
5826  {
5827  ImGui::MemFree(buf_local);
5828  buf_local = NULL;
5829  }
5830  if (!OpenClipboard(NULL))
5831  return NULL;
5832  HANDLE buf_handle = GetClipboardData(CF_TEXT);
5833  if (buf_handle == NULL)
5834  return NULL;
5835  if (char* buf_global = (char*)GlobalLock(buf_handle))
5836  buf_local = ImStrdup(buf_global);
5837  GlobalUnlock(buf_handle);
5838  CloseClipboard();
5839  return buf_local;
5840 }
5841 
5842 // Win32 API clipboard implementation
5843 static void SetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(const char* text)
5844 {
5845  if (!OpenClipboard(NULL))
5846  return;
5847  const char* text_end = text + strlen(text);
5848  const int buf_length = (int)(text_end - text) + 1;
5849  HGLOBAL buf_handle = GlobalAlloc(GMEM_MOVEABLE, buf_length * sizeof(char));
5850  if (buf_handle == NULL)
5851  return;
5852  char* buf_global = (char *)GlobalLock(buf_handle);
5853  memcpy(buf_global, text, text_end - text);
5854  buf_global[text_end - text] = 0;
5855  GlobalUnlock(buf_handle);
5856  EmptyClipboard();
5857  SetClipboardData(CF_TEXT, buf_handle);
5858  CloseClipboard();
5859 }
5860 
5861 #else
5862 
5863 // Local ImGui-only clipboard implementation, if user hasn't defined better clipboard handlers
5864 static const char* GetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl()
5865 {
5866  return GImGui.PrivateClipboard;
5867 }
5868 
5869 // Local ImGui-only clipboard implementation, if user hasn't defined better clipboard handlers
5870 static void SetClipboardTextFn_DefaultImpl(const char* text)
5871 {
5872  if (GImGui.PrivateClipboard)
5873  {
5874  ImGui::MemFree(GImGui.PrivateClipboard);
5875  GImGui.PrivateClipboard = NULL;
5876  }
5877  const char* text_end = text + strlen(text);
5878  GImGui.PrivateClipboard = (char*)ImGui::MemAlloc((size_t)(text_end - text) + 1);
5879  memcpy(GImGui.PrivateClipboard, text, (size_t)(text_end - text));
5880  GImGui.PrivateClipboard[(size_t)(text_end - text)] = 0;
5881 }
5882 
5883 #endif
